{"folder":"r7IGd9SqC2sfaO6M","name":"Protector","type":"flaw","img":"systems/arm5e/assets/icons/base-magic.svg","system":{"description":"<p>The covenant is responsible for protecting something, such as a village, a magical grove, or a weaker covenant. This Hook may be taken more than once, to represent multiple protectorates, and the site may be distant from the covenant.</p>","source":"Cov","page":25,"indexKey":"protector","review_status":"reviewed","reviewer":"lichen","type":"covenantSurroundings","impact":{"value":"minor"},"hidden":false,"tainted":false},"effects":[],"flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"12.343","systemId":"arm5e","systemVersion":"2.4.0.4","createdTime":1749287886938,"modifiedTime":1749370309871,"lastModifiedBy":"xMd6zrGNn4dbQYey"},"_id":"0dGVV8Kr4ZIbVxCs","sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J":3}}
{"folder":"of6RVKST8vt4Wki1","name":"Demonic Interest","type":"flaw","img":"systems/arm5e/assets/icons/base-magic.svg","system":{"description":"<p>This area has come to the particular attention of a powerful demon. It does not focus its attention entirely on the covenant, but it would like to claim the souls of the magi, and their servants, for Hell. The demon is served by a series of lesser Infernal spirits, and it sends them, usually one at a time, to oppress the area.</p>","source":"Cov","page":23,"indexKey":"demonic-interest","review_status":"reviewed","reviewer":"lichen","type":"covenantSurroundings","impact":{"value":"major"},"hidden":false,"tainted":false},"effects":[],"flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"12.343","systemId":"arm5e","systemVersion":"2.4.0.4","createdTime":1749287886938,"modifiedTime":1749370309894,"lastModifiedBy":"xMd6zrGNn4dbQYey"},"_id":"0daDh4XsvdleLMr7","sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J":3}}
{"folder":"r7IGd9SqC2sfaO6M","name":"Massacre Site","type":"flaw","img":"systems/arm5e/assets/icons/base-magic.svg","system":{"description":"<p>There is a piece of unhallowed ground near the covenant that was created by diabolism, battle, or some other terrible misfortune. Ghosts, animals possessed by demons, and clouds of illness come forth from it, and rumors of greater horrors are common. This Hook may be Unknown.</p>","source":"Cov","page":25,"indexKey":"massacre-site","review_status":"reviewed","reviewer":"lichen","type":"covenantSurroundings","impact":{"value":"minor"},"hidden":false,"tainted":false},"effects":[],"flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"12.343","systemId":"arm5e","systemVersion":"2.4.0.4","createdTime":1749287886938,"modifiedTime":1749370309916,"lastModifiedBy":"xMd6zrGNn4dbQYey"},"_id":"15oH2pvp5G1cix24","sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J":3}}
{"folder":"g2kV0ETU5Ech2O66","name":"Infants","type":"flaw","img":"systems/arm5e/assets/icons/base-magic.svg","system":{"description":"<p>Something about the covenant’s aura is affecting the next generation of covenfolk. In some covenants, the Hook is that every child born is a twin. Many women die in labor, the covenant’s population booms, and stories involving mistaken identity are common. As the population increases, the covenant needs to expand, possibly to the detriment of its neighbors. In other covenants children are very rare, which leads to folk and faerie remedies for bringing about pregnancy, the nurturing of children communally, and the constant need for immigrants. In some covenants, the children have odd flaws or skills, or are not human at all. This warping usually follows a single theme. In one Alpine covenant, for example, all people born are suited to temperatures far below the human norm.</p>","source":"Cov","page":20,"indexKey":"infants","review_status":"reviewed","reviewer":"lichen","type":"covenantResidents","impact":{"value":"minor"},"hidden":false,"tainted":false},"effects":[],"flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"12.343","systemId":"arm5e","systemVersion":"2.4.0.4","createdTime":1749287883937,"modifiedTime":1749370309933,"lastModifiedBy":"xMd6zrGNn4dbQYey"},"_id":"15qpM6yX83ht3gmd","sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J":3}}
{"folder":"BENb4deddxRJwwcu","name":"Flickering Aura","type":"flaw","img":"systems/arm5e/assets/icons/base-magic.svg","system":{"description":"<p>If the magi fail to perform a relatively simple task each year, the covenant’s aura declines by one point for the rest of the year. Flickering auras are usually the result of a traumatic mystical event that scars the spirit of a place. Magi who find ways to symbolically relive or repair the event can prevent their aura flickering. This is important, because flickering auras do not appear to deepen over time the way that auras in other covenants do. This Hook may be Unknown. </p><p>A particular covenant washes its walls each year in milk to prevent its aura from failing. The magi have no idea why, or even if, this is necessary, but it has been done since before the Schism War and dire, if painfully unspecific, warnings surround the practice.</p>","source":"Cov","page":10,"indexKey":"flickering-aura","review_status":"reviewed","reviewer":"lichen","type":"covenantSite","impact":{"value":"minor"},"hidden":false,"tainted":false},"effects":[],"flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"12.343","systemId":"arm5e","systemVersion":"2.4.0.4","createdTime":1749287885314,"modifiedTime":1749370309945,"lastModifiedBy":"xMd6zrGNn4dbQYey"},"_id":"1Cnw0t0OkE762Qeq","sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J":3}}
{"folder":"r7IGd9SqC2sfaO6M","name":"Hermit","type":"flaw","img":"systems/arm5e/assets/icons/base-magic.svg","system":{"description":"<p>A saintly hermit lives within the vicinity of the covenant. He does not meddle much in the affairs of mundane people, but is sometimes drawn from seclusion by visions. This Hook may be Unknown until the first encounter.</p>","source":"Cov","page":25,"indexKey":"hermit","review_status":"reviewed","reviewer":"lichen","type":"covenantSurroundings","impact":{"value":"minor"},"hidden":false,"tainted":false},"effects":[],"flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"12.343","systemId":"arm5e","systemVersion":"2.4.0.4","createdTime":1749287886938,"modifiedTime":1749370309955,"lastModifiedBy":"xMd6zrGNn4dbQYey"},"_id":"1FHR6E4ZY2J4dVpi","sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J":3}}
{"folder":"of6RVKST8vt4Wki1","name":"Meddlesome Saint","type":"flaw","img":"systems/arm5e/assets/icons/base-magic.svg","system":{"description":"<p>A saint takes special interest in this area, perhaps because her relics are held in a local church. The saint is the patron of a cause or profession, which she seeks to promote while simultaneously attempting to lead certain people back to the true path. A meddlesome saint is far worse than a meddlesome person, because saints are all but beyond Hermetic power.</p>","source":"Cov","page":23,"indexKey":"meddlesome-saint","review_status":"reviewed","reviewer":"lichen","type":"covenantSurroundings","impact":{"value":"major"},"hidden":false,"tainted":false},"effects":[],"flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"12.343","systemId":"arm5e","systemVersion":"2.4.0.4","createdTime":1749287886938,"modifiedTime":1749370309963,"lastModifiedBy":"xMd6zrGNn4dbQYey"},"_id":"1rF6o91BOAh7Y9My","sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J":3}}
{"folder":"BENb4deddxRJwwcu","name":"Mutable","type":"flaw","img":"systems/arm5e/assets/icons/base-magic.svg","system":{"description":"<p>The fabric of reality alters within the covenant in ways that unGifted humans find simple. For example, the covenant incarnates their passions as guides and mentors, or beautiful songs can change the time of day, the color of cloth, and the attractiveness of the singer.</p>","source":"Cov","page":10,"indexKey":"mutable","review_status":"reviewed","reviewer":"lichen","type":"covenantSite","impact":{"value":"minor"},"hidden":false,"tainted":false},"effects":[],"flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"12.343","systemId":"arm5e","systemVersion":"2.4.0.4","createdTime":1749287885314,"modifiedTime":1749370309974,"lastModifiedBy":"xMd6zrGNn4dbQYey"},"_id":"2kTdvEpKjNtijRzg","sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J":3}}
{"folder":"FvLHeGVEQh6UL4Jd","name":"Monster","type":"flaw","img":"systems/arm5e/assets/icons/base-magic.svg","system":{"description":"<p>A powerful mystical creature lives inside the covenant. The creature can be aligned with any realm, and is too powerful for the player characters to defeat at the beginning of the campaign. </p><p>Monsters are often large, and many are wily, but the Redcap Marco, who collected many strange tales, once remarked that a covenant had lost a tower to loveliness. When the maga Pallas passed away her lover, a nymph of unmatched beauty, began to mourn her immediately. Her grief was so great, and her attractiveness so intense, that it is said that whoever sees the inconsolable maiden falls immediately in love with her, and so refuses to disturb her mourning. The tower has gone unused for sixty years.</p>","source":"Cov","page":9,"indexKey":"monster","review_status":"reviewed","reviewer":"lichen","type":"covenantSite","impact":{"value":"major"},"hidden":false,"tainted":false},"effects":[],"flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"12.343","systemId":"arm5e","systemVersion":"2.4.0.4","createdTime":1749287885314,"modifiedTime":1749370309981,"lastModifiedBy":"xMd6zrGNn4dbQYey"},"_id":"3D7338zjJo4Q3MsD","sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J":3}}
{"folder":"g2kV0ETU5Ech2O66","name":"Gender Imbalance","type":"flaw","img":"systems/arm5e/assets/icons/base-magic.svg","system":{"description":"<p>The covenant has a deeply unbalanced gender division. This is common in new covenants, which tend to have many male servants, and those that have lost many men to war. Surrounding communities judge the covenant by their own standards, and so expect a group that is mostly male to expand its territory as a way of claiming wealth and women. A community that has few men will be considered leaderless, ill-garrisoned, and vulnerable. These stereotypes are usually inaccurate for covenants, leading to nasty and unnecessary confrontations with expansionist nobles.</p>","source":"Cov","page":19,"indexKey":"gender-imbalance","review_status":"reviewed","reviewer":"lichen","type":"covenantResidents","impact":{"value":"minor"},"hidden":false,"tainted":false},"effects":[],"flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"12.343","systemId":"arm5e","systemVersion":"2.4.0.4","createdTime":1749287883937,"modifiedTime":1749370309988,"lastModifiedBy":"xMd6zrGNn4dbQYey"},"_id":"4GQutVYIwAPMVHRg","sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J":3}}
{"folder":"O5LhN2J2Ed3J2OWc","name":"Mercer House","type":"flaw","img":"systems/arm5e/assets/icons/base-magic.svg","system":{"description":"<p>Part of the covenant is a Mercer House, a supply and storage facility dedicated to supporting the operations of House Mercere. Recaps often retire to the covenant’s town after they have served their term, and many raise families with covenfolk.</p>","source":"Cov","page":19,"indexKey":"mercer-house","review_status":"reviewed","reviewer":"lichen","type":"covenantResidents","impact":{"value":"major"},"hidden":false,"tainted":false},"effects":[],"flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"12.343","systemId":"arm5e","systemVersion":"2.4.0.4","createdTime":1749287883937,"modifiedTime":1749370309994,"lastModifiedBy":"xMd6zrGNn4dbQYey"},"_id":"4HClGcHVs44jll0l","sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J":3}}
{"folder":"0tTkM6zxVjQTvaf8","name":"Missing Founder","type":"flaw","img":"systems/arm5e/assets/icons/base-magic.svg","system":{"description":"<p>One of the covenant’s founders slipped from Hermetic history indecisively, and this causes the covenant difficulty. For example, rumors emerge that the founder thought gone lives on in Faerie, or someone appears from Arcadia claiming to be his son. Alternately, a will might be found in a book in at Durenmar that gives many of the covenant’s goods to an heir, debtor, or cause. This Hook may be Unknown in the sense that the resumption of the founder’s estate is unexpected.</p>","source":"Cov","page":22,"indexKey":"missing-founder","review_status":"reviewed","reviewer":"lichen","type":"covenantExternalRelations","impact":{"value":"minor"},"hidden":false,"tainted":false},"effects":[],"flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"12.343","systemId":"arm5e","systemVersion":"2.4.0.4","createdTime":1749287868926,"modifiedTime":1749370310003,"lastModifiedBy":"xMd6zrGNn4dbQYey"},"_id":"4cePz8TCGnHtwt5C","sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J":3}}
{"folder":"FvLHeGVEQh6UL4Jd","name":"Magical Disaster","type":"flaw","img":"systems/arm5e/assets/icons/base-magic.svg","system":{"description":"<p>Long ago, this was the site of a mystical tragedy. Many supernatural forces in the area press the local magi to cease work here, lest they repeat the mistakes of the past. Other forces encourage them, promising that — this time — all will be well. Some say that Durenmar is such a site.</p>","source":"Cov","page":9,"indexKey":"magical-disaster","review_status":"reviewed","reviewer":"lichen","type":"covenantSite","impact":{"value":"major"},"hidden":false,"tainted":false},"effects":[],"flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"12.343","systemId":"arm5e","systemVersion":"2.4.0.4","createdTime":1749287885314,"modifiedTime":1749370310009,"lastModifiedBy":"xMd6zrGNn4dbQYey"},"_id":"4o8Uq5kKoUfSzsmx","sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J":3}}
{"folder":"FvLHeGVEQh6UL4Jd","name":"Constantly Mobile","type":"flaw","img":"systems/arm5e/assets/icons/base-magic.svg","system":{"description":"<p>This covenant moves constantly. For example, the Covenant of Crisp Winds lives on a flotilla of ships, which follows a route around the Mediterranean to collect vis and trade goods at auspicious times. If the covenant were to cease moving, it would lose its income.</p>","source":"Cov","page":9,"indexKey":"constantly-mobile","review_status":"reviewed","reviewer":"lichen","type":"covenantSite","impact":{"value":"major"},"hidden":false,"tainted":false},"effects":[],"flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"12.343","systemId":"arm5e","systemVersion":"2.4.0.4","createdTime":1749287885314,"modifiedTime":1749370310015,"lastModifiedBy":"xMd6zrGNn4dbQYey"},"_id":"70kLusGCTFNfnYry","sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J":3}}
{"folder":"of6RVKST8vt4Wki1","name":"Pilgrimage Site","type":"flaw","img":"systems/arm5e/assets/icons/base-magic.svg","system":{"description":"<p>Pious people travel from across the kingdom to visit a holy shrine near the covenant. This means that the Church is more active and vigilant in the area than usual. As a partial recompense, there are large numbers of wealthy people traveling through the area, and many similarly situated covenants make money by providing services to pilgrims.</p>","source":"Cov","page":24,"indexKey":"pilgrimage-site","review_status":"reviewed","reviewer":"lichen","type":"covenantSurroundings","impact":{"value":"major"},"hidden":false,"tainted":false},"effects":[],"flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"12.343","systemId":"arm5e","systemVersion":"2.4.0.4","createdTime":1749287886938,"modifiedTime":1749370310023,"lastModifiedBy":"xMd6zrGNn4dbQYey"},"_id":"7qTdrdzYA2ffLHgy","sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J":3}}
{"folder":"r7IGd9SqC2sfaO6M","name":"Fated Feat","type":"flaw","img":"systems/arm5e/assets/icons/base-magic.svg","system":{"description":"<p>An incomplete prophecy is widely known in the area. It causes upheaval whenever someone attempts to complete it. For example, in a castle near a covenant in Wales, there is a horn that can be blown only by the true heir of the ancient kings. Anyone attempting to gain access to the horn is claiming the local nobleman has no right to rule, which leads to trouble, but the horn periodically disappears from the castle, as if seeking an owner. Similar prophecies lead people to disturb resting monsters throughout Mythic Europe.</p>","source":"Cov","page":24,"indexKey":"fated-feat","review_status":"reviewed","reviewer":"lichen","type":"covenantSurroundings","impact":{"value":"minor"},"hidden":false,"tainted":false},"effects":[],"flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"12.343","systemId":"arm5e","systemVersion":"2.4.0.4","createdTime":1749287886938,"modifiedTime":1749370310029,"lastModifiedBy":"xMd6zrGNn4dbQYey"},"_id":"7reLh7uLClz81KOh","sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J":3}}
{"folder":"r7IGd9SqC2sfaO6M","name":"Guardians","type":"flaw","img":"systems/arm5e/assets/icons/base-magic.svg","system":{"description":"<p>In ancient times a hedge magician bound guardians to a site near the covenant. A legend says that the guardians protect the magician’s treasure, but a second, and more troubling, story says that the guardians are the jailers of a monster the wizard could not kill. The local nobility have made it clear that they do not desire anyone to disturb the trouble sleeping at the site, so any investigation must be circumspect.</p>","source":"Cov","page":24,"indexKey":"guardians","review_status":"reviewed","reviewer":"lichen","type":"covenantSurroundings","impact":{"value":"minor"},"hidden":false,"tainted":false},"effects":[],"flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"12.343","systemId":"arm5e","systemVersion":"2.4.0.4","createdTime":1749287886938,"modifiedTime":1749370310042,"lastModifiedBy":"xMd6zrGNn4dbQYey"},"_id":"8FRmBVNNt4MR2GhC","sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J":3}}
{"folder":"of6RVKST8vt4Wki1","name":"City","type":"flaw","img":"systems/arm5e/assets/icons/base-magic.svg","system":{"description":"<p>The covenant lies near a city. This is very convenient for purchasing material, but can lead to problems for political reasons. Most cities desire to dominate their hinterland, but noblemen usually control the area around cities and are jealous of their prerogatives. A city is a rich source of revenue, so if these noblemen are sufficiently powerful, they wish to control the city themselves. This Hook places the covenant in the zone where the city and its neighbors play out their disputes.</p>","source":"Cov","page":23,"indexKey":"city","review_status":"reviewed","reviewer":"lichen","type":"covenantSurroundings","impact":{"value":"major"},"hidden":false,"tainted":false},"effects":[],"flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"12.343","systemId":"arm5e","systemVersion":"2.4.0.4","createdTime":1749287886938,"modifiedTime":1749370310050,"lastModifiedBy":"xMd6zrGNn4dbQYey"},"_id":"8OA3OrjesvaXWWD3","sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J":3}}
{"folder":"r7IGd9SqC2sfaO6M","name":"Death Prophecies","type":"flaw","img":"systems/arm5e/assets/icons/base-magic.svg","system":{"description":"<p>An apparition appears in the area to warn certain people that they are about to die. Many of these people seek to prevent their deaths using methods detrimental to their fellows. Some attempt to atone for their sins; others begin a final round of debauchery and murder.</p>","source":"Cov","page":24,"indexKey":"death-prophecies","review_status":"reviewed","reviewer":"lichen","type":"covenantSurroundings","impact":{"value":"minor"},"hidden":false,"tainted":false},"effects":[],"flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"12.343","systemId":"arm5e","systemVersion":"2.4.0.4","createdTime":1749287886938,"modifiedTime":1749370310059,"lastModifiedBy":"xMd6zrGNn4dbQYey"},"_id":"8rQ0YnJV9jqbThNa","sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J":3}}
{"folder":"k0vela35v1xs3g2S","name":"Beholden","type":"flaw","img":"systems/arm5e/assets/icons/base-magic.svg","system":{"description":"<p><span class=\"NormalTextRun SCXW97144508 BCX2\" data-ccp-parastyle=\"Ars Magica Text\"><span style=\"font-family: Times New Roman, 'Times New Roman_EmbeddedFont', 'Times New Roman_MSFontService', serif\">The covenant owes favors to someone or something, possibly another covenant, or possibly a mundane lord, bishop, or mystical creature. The external party can give the covenant orders, although the covenant gets to decide on the best way to carry them out.</span></span></p>","source":"ArM5Def","page":0,"indexKey":"beholden","review_status":"reviewed","reviewer":"xzotl","type":"covenantExternalRelations","impact":{"value":"major"},"hidden":false,"tainted":false},"effects":[],"flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"12.343","systemId":"arm5e","systemVersion":"2.4.0.4","createdTime":1749287868926,"modifiedTime":1749370310065,"lastModifiedBy":"xMd6zrGNn4dbQYey"},"_id":"98ZdL0MAEByQWXt4","sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J":3}}
{"folder":"r7IGd9SqC2sfaO6M","name":"Faerie Court","type":"flaw","img":"systems/arm5e/assets/icons/base-magic.svg","system":{"description":"<p>There is a faerie court somewhere near the covenant. A faerie court is usually limited to a small geographical area, like a woodland, lakebed, or ring of stones. It is an endless source of stories if sought out. Occasionally the faeries may leave the court, like the Hounds of Anwyn chasing the dead across Wales by night, or the Selkie King coming ashore to find a bride. This Hook may be Unknown.</p>","source":"Cov","page":24,"indexKey":"faerie-court","review_status":"reviewed","reviewer":"lichen","type":"covenantSurroundings","impact":{"value":"minor"},"hidden":false,"tainted":false},"effects":[],"flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"12.343","systemId":"arm5e","systemVersion":"2.4.0.4","createdTime":1749287886938,"modifiedTime":1749370310074,"lastModifiedBy":"xMd6zrGNn4dbQYey"},"_id":"9Ew8VwsEGDx05qqD","sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J":3}}
{"folder":"of6RVKST8vt4Wki1","name":"Pagans","type":"flaw","img":"systems/arm5e/assets/icons/base-magic.svg","system":{"description":"<p>The covenfolk of this community worship something other than the Christian God. This is likely to cause intense friction with the Church if discovered. If the object of their worship answers their prayers on a dependable basis, it must be bought separately as a Boon, most likely an Ally.</p>","source":"Cov","page":24,"indexKey":"pagans","review_status":"reviewed","reviewer":"lichen","type":"covenantSurroundings","impact":{"value":"major"},"hidden":false,"tainted":false},"effects":[],"flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"12.343","systemId":"arm5e","systemVersion":"2.4.0.4","createdTime":1749287886938,"modifiedTime":1749370310080,"lastModifiedBy":"xMd6zrGNn4dbQYey"},"_id":"9W0BsS9fCCar6RDY","sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J":3}}
{"folder":"BENb4deddxRJwwcu","name":"Faerie Aura","type":"flaw","img":"systems/arm5e/assets/icons/base-magic.svg","system":{"description":"<p>The covenant has a faerie, rather than a magical, aura. The faeries most familiar with the site are very interested in what the magi are doing, and consider any attempt to block their access to the site, by Aegis of the Hearth, for example, insulting. </p><p>There is a covenant in Ireland that has been built on a faerie hurling pitch. This game, which involves two large teams attempting to abduct a ball using clubs, is all but a war. The Courts of Summer and Winter in the area play it twice a year, and always seem surprised by the result. Given that the only other option is a pitched battle against the faeries on their covenant site twice a year, the magi allow the game to spill through their buildings, but have installed stout doors on their sancta. If the game is not played, it is said, then summer will never end in the crops of autumn, or winter will never bloom into spring.</p>","source":"Cov","page":10,"indexKey":"faerie-aura","review_status":"reviewed","reviewer":"lichen","type":"covenantSite","impact":{"value":"minor"},"hidden":false,"tainted":false},"effects":[],"flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"12.343","systemId":"arm5e","systemVersion":"2.4.0.4","createdTime":1749287885314,"modifiedTime":1749370310088,"lastModifiedBy":"xMd6zrGNn4dbQYey"},"_id":"AXNGqZ66Jrm3nkC9","sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J":3}}
{"folder":"0tTkM6zxVjQTvaf8","name":"Undemocratic Tribunal","type":"flaw","img":"systems/arm5e/assets/icons/base-magic.svg","system":{"description":"<p>Your Tribunal is dominated politically by an Autumn covenant, which is not interested in your welfare.</p>","source":"Cov","page":22,"indexKey":"undemocratic-tribunal","review_status":"reviewed","reviewer":"lichen","type":"covenantExternalRelations","impact":{"value":"minor"},"hidden":false,"tainted":false},"effects":[],"flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"12.343","systemId":"arm5e","systemVersion":"2.4.0.4","createdTime":1749287868926,"modifiedTime":1749370310094,"lastModifiedBy":"xMd6zrGNn4dbQYey"},"_id":"Ad6VHL73pY6t0hgA","sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J":3}}
{"folder":"r7IGd9SqC2sfaO6M","name":"Festival","type":"flaw","img":"systems/arm5e/assets/icons/base-magic.svg","system":{"description":"<p>A large number of the local peasants gather for festivals on certain occasions. This often inconveniences the magi. For example, the Irish Beltane Fire Festivals dispel minor Hermetic enchantments and curse witches, so those with The Gift must hide behind the Aegis of the Hearth on those evenings. Passion plays may be followed by troublesome miracles, or over-excited mobs.</p>","source":"Cov","page":24,"indexKey":"festival","review_status":"reviewed","reviewer":"lichen","type":"covenantSurroundings","impact":{"value":"minor"},"hidden":false,"tainted":false},"effects":[],"flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"12.343","systemId":"arm5e","systemVersion":"2.4.0.4","createdTime":1749287886938,"modifiedTime":1749370310099,"lastModifiedBy":"xMd6zrGNn4dbQYey"},"_id":"BZvtY2bqYn8MDbau","sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J":3}}
{"folder":"g2kV0ETU5Ech2O66","name":"Dark Secret","type":"flaw","img":"systems/arm5e/assets/icons/base-magic.svg","system":{"description":"<p>The leaders of the covenant harbor a secret that, if exposed, may lead to their ostracism or punishment. Although they have many resources available to quiet it, the secret seems to crop up every few years as a potential problem. This Hook may be Unknown.</p>","source":"Cov","page":19,"indexKey":"dark-secret","review_status":"reviewed","reviewer":"lichen","type":"covenantResidents","impact":{"value":"minor"},"hidden":false,"tainted":false},"effects":[],"flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"12.343","systemId":"arm5e","systemVersion":"2.4.0.4","createdTime":1749287883937,"modifiedTime":1749370310109,"lastModifiedBy":"xMd6zrGNn4dbQYey"},"_id":"CCIcMG9DrRbitYim","sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J":3}}
{"folder":"g2kV0ETU5Ech2O66","name":"Seed of Madness","type":"flaw","img":"systems/arm5e/assets/icons/base-magic.svg","system":{"description":"<p>Madness is common among the covenfolk, caused by Warping or extreme social trauma in previous generations.</p>","source":"Cov","page":20,"indexKey":"seed-of-madness","review_status":"reviewed","reviewer":"lichen","type":"covenantResidents","impact":{"value":"minor"},"hidden":false,"tainted":false},"effects":[],"flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"12.343","systemId":"arm5e","systemVersion":"2.4.0.4","createdTime":1749287883937,"modifiedTime":1749370310115,"lastModifiedBy":"xMd6zrGNn4dbQYey"},"_id":"CCyH8Erzo1KncGaA","sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J":3}}
{"folder":"k0vela35v1xs3g2S","name":"War Zone","type":"flaw","img":"systems/arm5e/assets/icons/base-magic.svg","system":{"description":"<p>The covenant lies between two powerful noble holdings that are at war. Each side requires the magi to join it. Failure to assist, on either side, may lead to reprisal because the warlord considers the covenant in league with his enemy. This Hook may be Unknown.</p>","source":"Cov","page":22,"indexKey":"war-zone","review_status":"reviewed","reviewer":"lichen","type":"covenantExternalRelations","impact":{"value":"major"},"hidden":false,"tainted":false},"effects":[],"flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"12.343","systemId":"arm5e","systemVersion":"2.4.0.4","createdTime":1749287868926,"modifiedTime":1749370310124,"lastModifiedBy":"xMd6zrGNn4dbQYey"},"_id":"CL3S1bTZim3BhWSs","sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J":3}}
{"folder":"0tTkM6zxVjQTvaf8","name":"Church Territories","type":"flaw","img":"systems/arm5e/assets/icons/base-magic.svg","system":{"description":"<p>Large parts of Europe accept a representative of the Church as their mundane noble. This is a Minor Hook, rather than a Free Choice, because the Church is less tolerant of heterodoxy — thoughts that may lead to sin — in its territories than lay rulers are. This Hook may be Unknown.</p>","source":"Cov","page":22,"indexKey":"church-territories","review_status":"reviewed","reviewer":"lichen","type":"covenantExternalRelations","impact":{"value":"minor"},"hidden":false,"tainted":false},"effects":[],"flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"12.343","systemId":"arm5e","systemVersion":"2.4.0.4","createdTime":1749287868926,"modifiedTime":1749370310129,"lastModifiedBy":"xMd6zrGNn4dbQYey"},"_id":"CmaV9UMakgCikNA5","sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J":3}}
{"folder":"r7IGd9SqC2sfaO6M","name":"Site of Weakness","type":"flaw","img":"systems/arm5e/assets/icons/base-magic.svg","system":{"description":"<p>A mystical site near the covenant could be used by the unscrupulous to harm people for miles around. For example, a faerie stone in Wales that unleashes terrible storms that destroy crops if water is poured upon it. Climbing Mount Pilatus in the Alps can generate similar storms. Another covenant guards a graveyard, because sleeping there causes terrible plagues to emerge from the Earth and blow across the countryside. This Hook may be Unknown.</p>","source":"Cov","page":25,"indexKey":"site-of-weakness","review_status":"reviewed","reviewer":"lichen","type":"covenantSurroundings","impact":{"value":"minor"},"hidden":false,"tainted":false},"effects":[],"flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"12.343","systemId":"arm5e","systemVersion":"2.4.0.4","createdTime":1749287886938,"modifiedTime":1749370310137,"lastModifiedBy":"xMd6zrGNn4dbQYey"},"_id":"DmoBwEpki0PUtnyM","sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J":3}}
{"folder":"O5LhN2J2Ed3J2OWc","name":"Superiors","type":"flaw","img":"systems/arm5e/assets/icons/base-magic.svg","system":{"description":"<p>The player characters can be given orders by the ranking members of the covenant, which they must obey.</p>","source":"Cov","page":19,"indexKey":"superiors","review_status":"reviewed","reviewer":"lichen","type":"covenantResidents","impact":{"value":"major"},"hidden":false,"tainted":false},"effects":[],"flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"12.343","systemId":"arm5e","systemVersion":"2.4.0.4","createdTime":1749287883937,"modifiedTime":1749370310144,"lastModifiedBy":"xMd6zrGNn4dbQYey"},"_id":"Ejj5OmXBZNjq1X4J","sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J":3}}
{"folder":"k0vela35v1xs3g2S","name":"Mundane Politics","type":"flaw","img":"systems/arm5e/assets/icons/base-magic.svg","system":{"description":"<p>The covenant is deeply ensnared in mundane politics and must keep the Quaesitores from becoming too interested in their activities.</p>","source":"Cov","page":21,"indexKey":"mundane-politics","review_status":"reviewed","reviewer":"lichen","type":"covenantExternalRelations","impact":{"value":"major"},"hidden":false,"tainted":false},"effects":[],"flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"12.343","systemId":"arm5e","systemVersion":"2.4.0.4","createdTime":1749287868926,"modifiedTime":1749370310149,"lastModifiedBy":"xMd6zrGNn4dbQYey"},"_id":"F3l3b2U8v6sVIrEh","sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J":3}}
{"folder":"of6RVKST8vt4Wki1","name":"Seat of Power","type":"flaw","img":"systems/arm5e/assets/icons/base-magic.svg","system":{"description":"<p>The covenant is near the primary residence of a great nobleman or a prince of the church. Either is capable of raising a large army, and jealous of his control of the sources of revenue within this area.</p>","source":"Cov","page":24,"indexKey":"seat-of-power","review_status":"reviewed","reviewer":"lichen","type":"covenantSurroundings","impact":{"value":"major"},"hidden":false,"tainted":false},"effects":[],"flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"12.343","systemId":"arm5e","systemVersion":"2.4.0.4","createdTime":1749287886938,"modifiedTime":1749370310158,"lastModifiedBy":"xMd6zrGNn4dbQYey"},"_id":"F9ynCKm27hnUJKoT","sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J":3}}
{"folder":"r7IGd9SqC2sfaO6M","name":"Heretics","type":"flaw","img":"systems/arm5e/assets/icons/base-magic.svg","system":{"description":"<p>A large number of people in the area surrounding the covenant hold views of which the Church is unlikely to approve, once they become aware of them. The Church’s initial response may be to send friars to the area in an attempt to draw the heretics back to the true faith, but if this fails, military action by the Church’s mundane allies may follow. This Hook may be Unknown.</p>","source":"Cov","page":25,"indexKey":"heretics","review_status":"reviewed","reviewer":"lichen","type":"covenantSurroundings","impact":{"value":"minor"},"hidden":false,"tainted":false},"effects":[],"flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"12.343","systemId":"arm5e","systemVersion":"2.4.0.4","createdTime":1749287886938,"modifiedTime":1749370310164,"lastModifiedBy":"xMd6zrGNn4dbQYey"},"_id":"FhYuVHH3DgKBOltU","sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J":3}}
{"folder":"BENb4deddxRJwwcu","name":"Contested Resource","type":"flaw","_id":"Fn38LRfkDMg1SWz5","img":"systems/arm5e/assets/icons/base-magic.svg","system":{"description":"<div class=\"OutlineElement Ltr SCXW224169566 BCX2\" style=\"direction: ltr;\"><p class=\"Paragraph SCXW224169566 BCX2\" style=\"font-weight: normal; font-style: normal; vertical-align: baseline; background-color: transparent; color: windowtext; margin: 7.8px 0px 0px; padding-left: 0px; padding-right: 0px; text-indent: 0px\"><span class=\"NormalTextRun SCXW224169566 BCX2\" data-ccp-parastyle=\"Ars Magica Text\"><span style=\"font-family: Times New Roman, 'Times New Roman_EmbeddedFont', 'Times New Roman_MSFontService', serif\">Access to one of the covenant's accessible resources is contested with someone, or something, else. Thus, getting the resource requires a story. As a rule, one story means that the resource is available for five years. The resource in question should be of sufficient importance that the magi will want to bother with the story.</span></span><span style=\"font-family: Times New Roman, 'Times New Roman_EmbeddedFont', 'Times New Roman_MSFontService', serif\"> </span></p></div><div class=\"OutlineElement Ltr SCXW224169566 BCX2\" style=\"direction: ltr;\"><p class=\"Paragraph SCXW224169566 BCX2\" style=\"font-weight: normal; font-style: normal; vertical-align: baseline; background-color: transparent; color: windowtext; margin: 7.8px 0px 0px; padding-left: 0px; padding-right: 0px; text-indent: 0px\"><span class=\"NormalTextRun SCXW224169566 BCX2\" data-ccp-parastyle=\"Ars Magica Text\"><span style=\"font-family: Times New Roman, 'Times New Roman_EmbeddedFont', 'Times New Roman_MSFontService', serif\">This Hook may be taken multiple times to cover multiple resources. It may be Unknown when the saga starts, and only become known when the first contest comes due.</span></span><span style=\"font-family: Times New Roman, 'Times New Roman_EmbeddedFont', 'Times New Roman_MSFontService', serif\"> </span></p></div><div class=\"OutlineElement Ltr SCXW224169566 BCX2\" style=\"direction: ltr;\"><p class=\"Paragraph SCXW224169566 BCX2\" style=\"font-weight: normal; font-style: normal; vertical-align: baseline; background-color: transparent; color: windowtext; margin: 7.8px 0px 0px; padding-left: 0px; padding-right: 0px; text-indent: 0px\"><span class=\"NormalTextRun SCXW224169566 BCX2\" data-ccp-parastyle=\"Ars Magica Text\"><span style=\"font-family: Times New Roman, 'Times New Roman_EmbeddedFont', 'Times New Roman_MSFontService', serif\"><strong>Favors:</strong> The covenant owes favors to someone or something, possibly another covenant, or possibly a mundane lord, bishop, or supernatural creature. This person cannot give the covenant orders, but the covenant is really obliged to help if they are in difficulties.</span></span><span style=\"font-family: Times New Roman, 'Times New Roman_EmbeddedFont', 'Times New Roman_MSFontService', serif\"> </span></p></div><div class=\"OutlineElement Ltr SCXW224169566 BCX2\" style=\"direction: ltr;\"><p class=\"Paragraph SCXW224169566 BCX2\" style=\"font-weight: normal; font-style: normal; vertical-align: baseline; background-color: transparent; color: windowtext; margin: 7.8px 0px 0px; padding-left: 0px; padding-right: 0px; text-indent: 0px\"><span class=\"NormalTextRun SCXW224169566 BCX2\" data-ccp-parastyle=\"Ars Magica Text\"><span style=\"font-family: Times New Roman, 'Times New Roman_EmbeddedFont', 'Times New Roman_MSFontService', serif\">This Hook could be Unknown, if the obligations were incurred by other members of the covenant who have neglected to tell the player characters.</span></span><span style=\"font-family: Times New Roman, 'Times New Roman_EmbeddedFont', 'Times New Roman_MSFontService', serif\"> </span></p></div>","source":"ArM5Def","page":0,"indexKey":"","review_status":"reviewed","reviewer":"xzotl","type":"covenantResources","impact":{"value":"minor"},"hidden":false,"tainted":false},"effects":[],"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J":3},"flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"12.331","systemId":"arm5e","systemVersion":"2.3.2.7","createdTime":1729836645962,"modifiedTime":1731255712520,"lastModifiedBy":"tBE5EmoIXLzf3maM"}}
{"folder":"of6RVKST8vt4Wki1","name":"Monster","type":"flaw","img":"systems/arm5e/assets/icons/base-magic.svg","system":{"description":"<p>A powerful mystical creature lives inside the covenant. The creature can be aligned with any realm, and should be too powerful for the player characters to defeat at the beginning of the saga.</p>","source":"Cov","page":24,"indexKey":"monster","review_status":"reviewed","reviewer":"lichen","type":"covenantSurroundings","impact":{"value":"major"},"hidden":false,"tainted":false},"effects":[],"flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"12.343","systemId":"arm5e","systemVersion":"2.4.0.4","createdTime":1749287886938,"modifiedTime":1749370310173,"lastModifiedBy":"xMd6zrGNn4dbQYey"},"_id":"GShN649eEaoulT78","sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J":3}}
{"folder":"k0vela35v1xs3g2S","name":"Rival","type":"flaw","img":"systems/arm5e/assets/icons/base-magic.svg","system":{"description":"<p>Someone or some group is working to destroy the covenant, and has the resources for this to be possible. Thus, the rival must be of comparable power to the covenant.</p>","source":"Cov","page":22,"indexKey":"rival","review_status":"reviewed","reviewer":"lichen","type":"covenantExternalRelations","impact":{"value":"major"},"hidden":false,"tainted":false},"effects":[],"flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"12.343","systemId":"arm5e","systemVersion":"2.4.0.4","createdTime":1749287868926,"modifiedTime":1749370310178,"lastModifiedBy":"xMd6zrGNn4dbQYey"},"_id":"GWoNLzai7lrdeG8p","sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J":3}}
{"folder":"BENb4deddxRJwwcu","name":"Troublesome Aura","type":"flaw","img":"systems/arm5e/assets/icons/base-magic.svg","system":{"description":"<p>The Magic aura of the covenant has an alignment that sometimes makes activities that should have been simple much harder, and thus provokes stories. An aura aligned to Perdo is an example, as would be one aligned to “rashness,” or “discourtesy.”</p>","source":"RoP:M","page":16,"indexKey":"troublesome-aura","review_status":"reviewed","reviewer":"lichen","type":"covenantSite","impact":{"value":"minor"},"hidden":false,"tainted":false},"effects":[],"flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"12.343","systemId":"arm5e","systemVersion":"2.4.0.4","createdTime":1749287885314,"modifiedTime":1749370310186,"lastModifiedBy":"xMd6zrGNn4dbQYey"},"_id":"H1hCeczysNYXAzTA","sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J":3}}
{"folder":"g2kV0ETU5Ech2O66","name":"Incompetent Covenfolk","type":"flaw","img":"systems/arm5e/assets/icons/base-magic.svg","system":{"description":"<p>Many covenfolk are dim-witted, unskilled, or accident-prone. This may be correctable.</p>","source":"Cov","page":20,"indexKey":"incompetent-covenfolk","review_status":"reviewed","reviewer":"lichen","type":"covenantResidents","impact":{"value":"minor"},"hidden":false,"tainted":false},"effects":[],"flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"12.343","systemId":"arm5e","systemVersion":"2.4.0.4","createdTime":1749287883937,"modifiedTime":1749370310191,"lastModifiedBy":"xMd6zrGNn4dbQYey"},"_id":"H2BrfqcsjTlcNz0u","sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J":3}}
{"folder":"r7IGd9SqC2sfaO6M","name":"Legendary Site","type":"flaw","img":"systems/arm5e/assets/icons/base-magic.svg","system":{"description":"<p>An important historical event took place close to the covenant. This affects the covenant occasionally because either the events have not yet resolved themselves or outsiders sometimes stir up the site seeking artifacts or historical legitimacy. The regiones around Tintagel in Cornwall, for example, lie at the heart of many Arthurian myths: Merlin might wake from his slumber, a meddling person might unsheathe the sword that wakes the sleeping knights, or a king might attempt to seize the Round Table as it rises from a bog each midsummer and anger the faeries by his success or seek the aid of magi after his failure.</p>","source":"Cov","page":25,"indexKey":"legendary-site","review_status":"reviewed","reviewer":"lichen","type":"covenantSurroundings","impact":{"value":"minor"},"hidden":false,"tainted":false},"effects":[],"flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"12.343","systemId":"arm5e","systemVersion":"2.4.0.4","createdTime":1749287886938,"modifiedTime":1749370310197,"lastModifiedBy":"xMd6zrGNn4dbQYey"},"_id":"HJhAf3G7t39CCzoD","sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J":3}}
{"folder":"g2kV0ETU5Ech2O66","name":"Fosterage","type":"flaw","img":"systems/arm5e/assets/icons/base-magic.svg","system":{"description":"<p>The covenant is home to the child of a powerful person or being, either because the being wishes the child to be raised among magi, or because the magi have demanded it as a concession for other services. This child’s safety is paramount.</p>","source":"Cov","page":19,"indexKey":"fosterage","review_status":"reviewed","reviewer":"lichen","type":"covenantResidents","impact":{"value":"minor"},"hidden":false,"tainted":false},"effects":[],"flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"12.343","systemId":"arm5e","systemVersion":"2.4.0.4","createdTime":1749287883937,"modifiedTime":1749370310206,"lastModifiedBy":"xMd6zrGNn4dbQYey"},"_id":"HTJst65So62npfV1","sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J":3}}
{"folder":"of6RVKST8vt4Wki1","name":"Faerie Landlord","type":"flaw","img":"systems/arm5e/assets/icons/base-magic.svg","system":{"description":"<p>A powerful faerie claims all of the territory that the covenant uses, and is easily angered by its activities. The landlord has extensive magical abilities and many spies. An example is the giant Idris, who controls all of the land around the mountain that bears his name, in Wales. He can call down mist over the land, ruin crops with foul weather, and send his servants — gray foxes who can seep into houses like clouds — to spy on and sabotage his enemies.</p>","source":"Cov","page":23,"indexKey":"faerie-landlord","review_status":"reviewed","reviewer":"lichen","type":"covenantSurroundings","impact":{"value":"major"},"hidden":false,"tainted":false},"effects":[],"flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"12.343","systemId":"arm5e","systemVersion":"2.4.0.4","createdTime":1749287886938,"modifiedTime":1749370310213,"lastModifiedBy":"xMd6zrGNn4dbQYey"},"_id":"HW44de7oaVYSktWb","sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J":3}}
{"folder":"g2kV0ETU5Ech2O66","name":"Distorted Covenfolk","type":"flaw","img":"systems/arm5e/assets/icons/base-magic.svg","system":{"description":"<p>The natives of the covenant have been distorted by its aura, so they find it difficult to interact with mundane people, or travel in the mundane world.</p>","source":"Cov","page":19,"indexKey":"distorted-covenfolk","review_status":"reviewed","reviewer":"lichen","type":"covenantResidents","impact":{"value":"minor"},"hidden":false,"tainted":false},"effects":[],"flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"12.343","systemId":"arm5e","systemVersion":"2.4.0.4","createdTime":1749287883937,"modifiedTime":1749370310220,"lastModifiedBy":"xMd6zrGNn4dbQYey"},"_id":"HY0vcxucCBYqBesC","sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J":3}}
{"folder":"r7IGd9SqC2sfaO6M","name":"Deathbed Visitor","type":"flaw","img":"systems/arm5e/assets/icons/base-magic.svg","system":{"description":"<p>A supernatural being appears to many people in the surrounding area as they are about to die. In some areas, it is Death himself; in others, demons come seeking the souls of sinners. If this visitor can be tricked, or beaten in a game in which the dying individual wagers his life or soul, then the dying person might be saved.</p>","source":"Cov","page":24,"indexKey":"deathbed-visitor","review_status":"reviewed","reviewer":"lichen","type":"covenantSurroundings","impact":{"value":"minor"},"hidden":false,"tainted":false},"effects":[],"flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"12.343","systemId":"arm5e","systemVersion":"2.4.0.4","createdTime":1749287886938,"modifiedTime":1749370310226,"lastModifiedBy":"xMd6zrGNn4dbQYey"},"_id":"HnmhTHFohEB2y1Nw","sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J":3}}
{"folder":"BENb4deddxRJwwcu","name":"Regio","type":"flaw","img":"systems/arm5e/assets/icons/base-magic.svg","system":{"description":"<p>There is a regio on the covenant site, although the covenant does not lie within it. The magi do not know everything that is in the regio. </p><p>If the regio is not magical, that counts as an additional Minor Hook. This Hook can still be taken if the covenant is in a regio; in that case, it simply refers to a second regio.</p>","source":"Cov","page":10,"indexKey":"regio","review_status":"reviewed","reviewer":"lichen","type":"covenantSite","impact":{"value":"minor"},"hidden":false,"tainted":false},"effects":[],"flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"12.343","systemId":"arm5e","systemVersion":"2.4.0.4","createdTime":1749287885314,"modifiedTime":1749370310232,"lastModifiedBy":"xMd6zrGNn4dbQYey"},"_id":"HvNkc8VbanYdlyRn","sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J":3}}
{"folder":"g2kV0ETU5Ech2O66","name":"Superiors","type":"flaw","img":"systems/arm5e/assets/icons/base-magic.svg","system":{"description":"<p>The player characters are not in charge of the covenant, and while their superiors cannot order them about, the player characters do not have control of covenant resources.</p>","source":"Cov","page":20,"indexKey":"superiors","review_status":"reviewed","reviewer":"lichen","type":"covenantResidents","impact":{"value":"minor"},"hidden":false,"tainted":false},"effects":[],"flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"12.343","systemId":"arm5e","systemVersion":"2.4.0.4","createdTime":1749287883937,"modifiedTime":1749370310242,"lastModifiedBy":"xMd6zrGNn4dbQYey"},"_id":"HvPmfFZnDpLwZ1Tp","sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J":3}}
{"folder":"of6RVKST8vt4Wki1","name":"Enclosed","type":"flaw","img":"systems/arm5e/assets/icons/base-magic.svg","system":{"description":"<p>Forces that the magi cannot currently counter have prevented all mundane travel to the rest of the world. This has the advantage of making the covenant safe from prying priests and noblemen, but leaves the covenant vulnerable to shortages of materials and skilled laborers. Any surplus the covenant produces for trade is likely valueless, as are portable forms of wealth like precious metal and gemstones, since there are no buyers for these goods available. They may be stored until the covenant connects with the outside world.</p>","source":"Cov","page":23,"indexKey":"enclosed","review_status":"reviewed","reviewer":"lichen","type":"covenantSurroundings","impact":{"value":"major"},"hidden":false,"tainted":false},"effects":[],"flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"12.343","systemId":"arm5e","systemVersion":"2.4.0.4","createdTime":1749287886938,"modifiedTime":1749370310247,"lastModifiedBy":"xMd6zrGNn4dbQYey"},"_id":"IdegkGsSVen5u7dN","sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J":3}}
{"folder":"r7IGd9SqC2sfaO6M","name":"Roman Ruins","type":"flaw","img":"systems/arm5e/assets/icons/base-magic.svg","system":{"description":"<p>A ruined Roman fort, wall, or township lies near the covenant. Rumors say it is intermittently haunted, and some treasure may remain, hidden nearby. The ruin’s chief use to magi is that it is made of dressed stone, which can be reused to make covenant buildings, if they can secure the rights to it from its owners. This Hook may be Unknown.</p>","source":"Cov","page":25,"indexKey":"roman-ruins","review_status":"reviewed","reviewer":"lichen","type":"covenantSurroundings","impact":{"value":"minor"},"hidden":false,"tainted":false},"effects":[],"flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"12.343","systemId":"arm5e","systemVersion":"2.4.0.4","createdTime":1749287886938,"modifiedTime":1749370310255,"lastModifiedBy":"xMd6zrGNn4dbQYey"},"_id":"Ii4PVsa0JyXhohD0","sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J":3}}
{"folder":"k0vela35v1xs3g2S","name":"Tribunal Border","type":"flaw","img":"systems/arm5e/assets/icons/base-magic.svg","system":{"description":"<p>The covenant lies outside any Tribunal, or in the disputed borderland between two Tribunals. Representatives of powerful covenants in the neighboring Tribunals attempt to sway the magi to join their Tribunal when the magi are forced to select one. Slighted suitors may be angered.</p>","source":"Cov","page":22,"indexKey":"tribunal-border","review_status":"reviewed","reviewer":"lichen","type":"covenantExternalRelations","impact":{"value":"major"},"hidden":false,"tainted":false},"effects":[],"flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"12.343","systemId":"arm5e","systemVersion":"2.4.0.4","createdTime":1749287868926,"modifiedTime":1749370310260,"lastModifiedBy":"xMd6zrGNn4dbQYey"},"_id":"JBG6R9kF1evdWCeD","sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J":3}}
{"folder":"g2kV0ETU5Ech2O66","name":"House Church","type":"flaw","img":"systems/arm5e/assets/icons/base-magic.svg","system":{"description":"<p>A fervent group of Christians practices the sacraments in one of the houses within the covenant. Left unchecked, this may affect the aura. An added complication is that the House Church members may be heretics, living in the covenant as a shelter from the Church. This Hook may be Unknown.</p>","source":"Cov","page":20,"indexKey":"house-church","review_status":"reviewed","reviewer":"lichen","type":"covenantResidents","impact":{"value":"minor"},"hidden":false,"tainted":false},"effects":[],"flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"12.343","systemId":"arm5e","systemVersion":"2.4.0.4","createdTime":1749287883937,"modifiedTime":1749370310266,"lastModifiedBy":"xMd6zrGNn4dbQYey"},"_id":"JOssgPNIixMtknHY","sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J":3}}
{"folder":"0tTkM6zxVjQTvaf8","name":"Public Vis Source","type":"flaw","img":"systems/arm5e/assets/icons/base-magic.svg","system":{"description":"<p>One or more of the covenant’s vis sources has had its location and method of harvesting precisely written into a ruling of the Peripheral Code. The covenant unquestionably owns the source, but any enemy wishing to make mischief knows exactly where the covenant’s vis comes from.</p>","source":"Cov","page":22,"indexKey":"public-vis-source","review_status":"reviewed","reviewer":"lichen","type":"covenantExternalRelations","impact":{"value":"minor"},"hidden":false,"tainted":false},"effects":[],"flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"12.343","systemId":"arm5e","systemVersion":"2.4.0.4","createdTime":1749287868926,"modifiedTime":1749370310274,"lastModifiedBy":"xMd6zrGNn4dbQYey"},"_id":"Jac31ydiVUxBgx1U","sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J":3}}
{"folder":"r7IGd9SqC2sfaO6M","name":"Sanctuary","type":"flaw","img":"systems/arm5e/assets/icons/base-magic.svg","system":{"description":"<p>A site near the covenant is a sanctuary: a place where the accused can shelter, either due to ancient law or because it is owned by the Church. Sanctuaries tend to attract desperate criminals, and innocents who are even more desperate. This Hook may be Unknown.</p>","source":"Cov","page":25,"indexKey":"sanctuary","review_status":"reviewed","reviewer":"lichen","type":"covenantSurroundings","impact":{"value":"minor"},"hidden":false,"tainted":false},"effects":[],"flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"12.343","systemId":"arm5e","systemVersion":"2.4.0.4","createdTime":1749287886938,"modifiedTime":1749370310279,"lastModifiedBy":"xMd6zrGNn4dbQYey"},"_id":"JoavXBkJboCzcajo","sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J":3}}
{"folder":"BENb4deddxRJwwcu","name":"Evil Custom","type":"flaw","img":"systems/arm5e/assets/icons/base-magic.svg","system":{"description":"<p>Some of the mystical features of the covenant’s site are maintained through ritual acts that are evil, but of so long a tradition that most people in the area are aware of them, and so simply avoid being suitable victims. Many evil customs involve murder, but some simply require the imprisonment of a certain person for a time, the humiliation of a class of people, or sins of gross indulgence. This Hook may be Unknown.</p>","source":"Cov","page":10,"indexKey":"evil-custom","review_status":"reviewed","reviewer":"lichen","type":"covenantSite","impact":{"value":"minor"},"hidden":false,"tainted":false},"effects":[],"flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"12.343","systemId":"arm5e","systemVersion":"2.4.0.4","createdTime":1749287885314,"modifiedTime":1749370310287,"lastModifiedBy":"xMd6zrGNn4dbQYey"},"_id":"KpkknKj2kCD9lfyW","sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J":3}}
{"folder":"r7IGd9SqC2sfaO6M","name":"Missing Expedition","type":"flaw","img":"systems/arm5e/assets/icons/base-magic.svg","system":{"description":"<p>A group of Hermetic magi attempted to set up a covenant in this area many years ago, but they vanished. Clues to their fate may emerge, and whatever happened to them might threaten to recur. This Hook may be Unknown.</p>","source":"Cov","page":25,"indexKey":"missing-expedition","review_status":"reviewed","reviewer":"lichen","type":"covenantSurroundings","impact":{"value":"minor"},"hidden":false,"tainted":false},"effects":[],"flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"12.343","systemId":"arm5e","systemVersion":"2.4.0.4","createdTime":1749287886938,"modifiedTime":1749370310293,"lastModifiedBy":"xMd6zrGNn4dbQYey"},"_id":"LEBEaoTS0T1FAYRs","sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J":3}}
{"folder":"BENb4deddxRJwwcu","name":"Unhealthy Feature","type":"flaw","img":"systems/arm5e/assets/icons/base-magic.svg","system":{"description":"<p>The covenant’s members suffer a dramatically reduced lifespan due to an environmental factor at the covenant’s site. All people regularly exposed to the environmental factor suffer a –1 penalty to their Aging rolls. This Hook may be taken up to three times, but does not affect those who have Hermetic longevity enchantments. </p><p>This condition is a Hook because these environmental problems are often reparable with magic or labor. For example, a covenant where people suffer the miasmatic effects of a nearby swamp can ameliorate this effect in several ways. Cutting channels to a nearby river, or a magical effect, could drain the swamp. The miasma might be destroyed with magic. It might be rendered ineffective by planting of an orchard of sweetly flowering trees as a defensive perimeter. Deeply noxious environmental conditions might have mystical defenders, like bog trolls, which would have to be dealt with before the Hook itself could be eliminated. </p><p>This Boon may be Unknown, but becomes known as an increasing number of covenfolk feel its effects.</p>","source":"Cov","page":11,"indexKey":"unhealthy-feature","review_status":"reviewed","reviewer":"lichen","type":"covenantSite","impact":{"value":"minor"},"hidden":false,"tainted":false},"effects":[],"flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"12.343","systemId":"arm5e","systemVersion":"2.4.0.4","createdTime":1749287885314,"modifiedTime":1749370310299,"lastModifiedBy":"xMd6zrGNn4dbQYey"},"_id":"N2FrZqSOH0g5qcM1","sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J":3}}
{"folder":"egD6BYeMAt02SJl1","name":"Wooden","type":"flaw","img":"systems/arm5e/assets/icons/base-magic.svg","system":{"description":"<p>A large number of medieval castles are made of wood. These are particularly vulnerable to fire, and, since Hermetic laboratories are one of the very few sources of explosions in Mythic Europe, Hermetic magi prefer to avoid or upgrade them. They are, however, cheap and quick to construct, and so may be suitable for Spring covenants, particularly those in forests.</p>","source":"Cov","page":15,"indexKey":"wooden","review_status":"reviewed","reviewer":"lichen","type":"other","impact":{"value":"minor"},"hidden":false,"tainted":false},"effects":[],"flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"12.343","systemId":"arm5e","systemVersion":"2.4.0.4","createdTime":1749287871166,"modifiedTime":1749370310308,"lastModifiedBy":"xMd6zrGNn4dbQYey"},"_id":"NAnUmWzpJvPSAXpJ","sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J":3}}
{"folder":"O5LhN2J2Ed3J2OWc","name":"Fractured Council","type":"flaw","img":"systems/arm5e/assets/icons/base-magic.svg","system":{"description":"<p>The covenant’s magi do not work together. This may be because of chronically poor organization, psychological damage from Warping, rivalry, misanthropy, or mutual hatred. Covenants dominated by player characters may not take this Hook (or, at least, do not get a Boon in return).</p>","source":"Cov","page":19,"indexKey":"fractured-council","review_status":"reviewed","reviewer":"lichen","type":"covenantResidents","impact":{"value":"major"},"hidden":false,"tainted":false},"effects":[],"flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"12.343","systemId":"arm5e","systemVersion":"2.4.0.4","createdTime":1749287883937,"modifiedTime":1749370310314,"lastModifiedBy":"xMd6zrGNn4dbQYey"},"_id":"O09xQd3zzPJF9TQH","sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J":3}}
{"folder":"g2kV0ETU5Ech2O66","name":"Inhuman Covenfolk","type":"flaw","img":"systems/arm5e/assets/icons/base-magic.svg","system":{"description":"<p>Enough of the covenant’s residents are inhuman that it draws attention from surrounding communities. They become aware of the inhuman population far more quickly if they engage in militancy or commerce.</p>","source":"Cov","page":20,"indexKey":"inhuman-covenfolk","review_status":"reviewed","reviewer":"lichen","type":"covenantResidents","impact":{"value":"minor"},"hidden":false,"tainted":false},"effects":[],"flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"12.343","systemId":"arm5e","systemVersion":"2.4.0.4","createdTime":1749287883937,"modifiedTime":1749370310322,"lastModifiedBy":"xMd6zrGNn4dbQYey"},"_id":"OsTd9pCmEHZXQokR","sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J":3}}
{"folder":"FvLHeGVEQh6UL4Jd","name":"Highly Mutable","type":"flaw","img":"systems/arm5e/assets/icons/base-magic.svg","system":{"description":"<p>The contents of the covenant’s aura, with the exception of the human beings, whose souls provide them protection from this effect, are highly mutable. The method of mutation varies between sites, and is difficult for the magi to predict or control. </p><p>For example, Marco, a Redcap known for telling lies, states that there is a covenant in a regio that mirrors the dreams of the people of a city he will not name. If the city suffers a fire, then the covenant also suffers a fire. If a ship of exotic merchants land and many people dream of England, the weather becomes icy and annoying. If a passion play is performed, many phantasms with the shape of demons (but not their nature) rampage through the covenant, unblocked by the Aegis (for they have no Might). The magi stay there because the area within the Aegis remains much the same functionally, although its appearance changes from a Norman town to a Jewish ghetto to what people think an Arabic trading quarter must look like, and they find these insights into the human mind fascinating.</p>","source":"Cov","page":9,"indexKey":"highly-mutable","review_status":"reviewed","reviewer":"lichen","type":"covenantSite","impact":{"value":"major"},"hidden":false,"tainted":false},"effects":[],"flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"12.343","systemId":"arm5e","systemVersion":"2.4.0.4","createdTime":1749287885314,"modifiedTime":1749370310327,"lastModifiedBy":"xMd6zrGNn4dbQYey"},"_id":"PbC5gHFc8ReXWuX7","sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J":3}}
{"folder":"0tTkM6zxVjQTvaf8","name":"Slavery","type":"flaw","img":"systems/arm5e/assets/icons/base-magic.svg","system":{"description":"<p>Your covenant has slaves in its population. It is illegal, in Europe, to enslave Christians, so enslaved populations are rare in Hermetic covenants. There are some Hermetic slaves in the Baltic, and others in the Levantine and Theban Tribunals, purchased after the fall of Damietta to the Crusaders last year. Slaves who convert must be freed.</p>","source":"Cov","page":22,"indexKey":"slavery","review_status":"reviewed","reviewer":"lichen","type":"covenantExternalRelations","impact":{"value":"minor"},"hidden":false,"tainted":false},"effects":[],"flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"12.343","systemId":"arm5e","systemVersion":"2.4.0.4","createdTime":1749287868926,"modifiedTime":1749370310334,"lastModifiedBy":"xMd6zrGNn4dbQYey"},"_id":"Q5k15bKBLKw4yB6Q","sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J":3}}
{"folder":"g2kV0ETU5Ech2O66","name":"Suffrage","type":"flaw","img":"systems/arm5e/assets/icons/base-magic.svg","system":{"description":"<p>The covenant grants equal rights to men and women. This is, theoretically, sinful and likely to incite contempt of the covenant’s officials by outsiders.</p>","source":"Cov","page":20,"indexKey":"suffrage","review_status":"reviewed","reviewer":"lichen","type":"covenantResidents","impact":{"value":"minor"},"hidden":false,"tainted":false},"effects":[],"flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"12.343","systemId":"arm5e","systemVersion":"2.4.0.4","createdTime":1749287883937,"modifiedTime":1749370310344,"lastModifiedBy":"xMd6zrGNn4dbQYey"},"_id":"RIgbI5UMCPsQHqrs","sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J":3}}
{"folder":"O5LhN2J2Ed3J2OWc","name":"School","type":"flaw","img":"systems/arm5e/assets/icons/base-magic.svg","system":{"description":"<p>The younger sons of many rich farmers and lesser lords congregate at the covenant to be taught letters and something of philosophy. Some travel to the covenant from surrounding farms each day, while many from further away board for much of the year. Their training is insufficient to work as clerks or jurists, but it prepares them for later, university study and marks them as gentry. </p><p>House Jerbiton runs several of these schools. Jerbiton apprentices are usually Gently Gifted, so they are more difficult to detect than those of other Houses. Schoolmasters seek signs of magical ability or precocious intelligence among their charges, then report promising students to the magi. House Jerbiton also runs schools for girls, which is a novelty for many noblemen.</p>","source":"Cov","page":19,"indexKey":"school","review_status":"reviewed","reviewer":"lichen","type":"covenantResidents","impact":{"value":"major"},"hidden":false,"tainted":false},"effects":[],"flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"12.343","systemId":"arm5e","systemVersion":"2.4.0.4","createdTime":1749287883937,"modifiedTime":1749370310352,"lastModifiedBy":"xMd6zrGNn4dbQYey"},"_id":"UZeGQhL11t7fcqnW","sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J":3}}
{"folder":"BENb4deddxRJwwcu","name":"Warping to a Pattern","type":"flaw","img":"systems/arm5e/assets/icons/base-magic.svg","system":{"description":"<p>The Warping suffered by people, animals, and structures within the covenant is not random or restricted to a single motif. Rather, a discernible theme runs through the distortions. Characters familiar with the history of the site, the dreams of its founders, the epics of the ancients, and the folklore of the Order can sometimes explain the evolving theme, which is often a repetition of something that has been experienced before. </p><p>It is said that the site of the Covenant of the Monkey’s Reed has not forgotten its history. Located on a floating island, which moves about its lake, the aura is slowly twisting the people and structures of the covenant into an ancient Egyptian village. The rulers of the village were a priestly caste that worshiped the god Thoth. </p><p>Many magi of Monkey’s Reed wish to see what these ancient magicians looked like, reflected in the covenant’s aura, but there is a problem: the site replaces the memories of those it distorts, so that they gradually lose themselves in their new roles. Magi of House Bonisagus hope to convince the Archimagus Apollodarus — whose beloved died accidentally in a fire that he created — that he should accept the loss of memory as a balm and become High Priest of the Temple that, even now, can be seen forming in the brickwork of the gatehouse.</p>","source":"Cov","page":11,"indexKey":"warping-to-a-pattern","review_status":"reviewed","reviewer":"lichen","type":"covenantSite","impact":{"value":"minor"},"hidden":false,"tainted":false},"effects":[],"flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"12.343","systemId":"arm5e","systemVersion":"2.4.0.4","createdTime":1749287885314,"modifiedTime":1749370310359,"lastModifiedBy":"xMd6zrGNn4dbQYey"},"_id":"UfOviScvovOU6IYz","sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J":3}}
{"folder":"k0vela35v1xs3g2S","name":"Center of Exellence","type":"flaw","img":"systems/arm5e/assets/icons/base-magic.svg","system":{"description":"<p>The covenant lies close to a mundane source of unusual goods, and employs specialists to make those goods. The rulers of the place that provides the materials, who are extremely wealthy, will grow to see the covenant as a threat to their monopoly. Examples include glass manufacture near Venice and silk near Constantinople.</p>","source":"Cov","page":21,"indexKey":"center-of-exellence","review_status":"reviewed","reviewer":"lichen","type":"covenantExternalRelations","impact":{"value":"major"},"hidden":false,"tainted":false},"effects":[],"flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"12.343","systemId":"arm5e","systemVersion":"2.4.0.4","createdTime":1749287868926,"modifiedTime":1749370310365,"lastModifiedBy":"xMd6zrGNn4dbQYey"},"_id":"Vf3jadRQM6XRqguN","sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J":3}}
{"folder":"0tTkM6zxVjQTvaf8","name":"Favors","type":"flaw","img":"systems/arm5e/assets/icons/base-magic.svg","system":{"description":"<p>The covenant owes favors to someone or something, possibly another covenant, or possibly a mundane lord, bishop, or mystical creature. This person cannot give the covenant orders, but the covenant is really obliged to help if he is in difficulty.</p>","source":"Cov","page":22,"indexKey":"favors","review_status":"reviewed","reviewer":"lichen","type":"covenantExternalRelations","impact":{"value":"minor"},"hidden":false,"tainted":false},"effects":[],"flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"12.343","systemId":"arm5e","systemVersion":"2.4.0.4","createdTime":1749287868926,"modifiedTime":1749370310373,"lastModifiedBy":"xMd6zrGNn4dbQYey"},"_id":"X4zGclUZaiwBrQw5","sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J":3}}
{"folder":"BENb4deddxRJwwcu","name":"Cursed","type":"flaw","img":"systems/arm5e/assets/icons/base-magic.svg","system":{"description":"<p>The covenant is the victim of a supernatural curse powerful enough to ignore its Aegis of the Hearth. This should gravely concern the magi, because it indicates they have a supernatural enemy with both the desire and ability to harm them. This Hook may be Unknown. </p><p>Most curses of this type are not fatal. For example, magi from one covenant refused the hospitality of a faerie crone, and now suffer fatal burns if they taste wine, as it turns into green vitriol. The crone, fair-minded, warned the magi of the curse, so it has killed only one magus. New to Normandy, and not skilled in French, he foolishly ordered the coq au vin.</p>","source":"Cov","page":10,"indexKey":"cursed","review_status":"reviewed","reviewer":"lichen","type":"covenantSite","impact":{"value":"minor"},"hidden":false,"tainted":false},"effects":[],"flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"12.343","systemId":"arm5e","systemVersion":"2.4.0.4","createdTime":1749287885314,"modifiedTime":1749370310379,"lastModifiedBy":"xMd6zrGNn4dbQYey"},"_id":"XDHMJaUunrmwg12Z","sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J":3}}
{"folder":"BENb4deddxRJwwcu","name":"Corrupt Area","type":"flaw","img":"systems/arm5e/assets/icons/base-magic.svg","system":{"description":"<p>A section of the covenant has an Infernal aura, probably because of a terrible sin committed there. This acts as a seed for the corruption of the covenant, unless the characters discover the nature of the event and put things right. This Hook may be Unknown.</p>","source":"Cov","page":10,"indexKey":"corrupt-area","review_status":"reviewed","reviewer":"lichen","type":"covenantSite","impact":{"value":"minor"},"hidden":false,"tainted":false},"effects":[],"flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"12.343","systemId":"arm5e","systemVersion":"2.4.0.4","createdTime":1749287885314,"modifiedTime":1749370310386,"lastModifiedBy":"xMd6zrGNn4dbQYey"},"_id":"Y3K0W6cq9JXm4v7H","sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J":3}}
{"folder":"g2kV0ETU5Ech2O66","name":"Possession Victim","type":"flaw","img":"systems/arm5e/assets/icons/base-magic.svg","system":{"description":"<p>One of the covenfolk is possessed by a powerful demon. It has been able to cross the Aegis of the Hearth hidden in its host. It seeks to do harm and convert others to its service. This Hook is usually Unknown.</p>","source":"Cov","page":20,"indexKey":"possession-victim","review_status":"reviewed","reviewer":"lichen","type":"covenantResidents","impact":{"value":"minor"},"hidden":false,"tainted":false},"effects":[],"flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"12.343","systemId":"arm5e","systemVersion":"2.4.0.4","createdTime":1749287883937,"modifiedTime":1749370310393,"lastModifiedBy":"xMd6zrGNn4dbQYey"},"_id":"YDUzRpi2In4W2n5T","sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J":3}}
{"folder":"0tTkM6zxVjQTvaf8","name":"Unsafe","type":"flaw","img":"systems/arm5e/assets/icons/base-magic.svg","system":{"description":"<p>Redcaps do not visit your covenant. The usual reason the House gives for this lack of service is that the way is too unsafe even for the brave and resourceful servants of the House, although this excuse occasionally hides another motive. Instead of direct delivery, the covenant’s servants collect messages at a Mercer House or secure drop-off point. This delay means that the letters are sometimes worthless, opportunities for action having passed. The covenant can have normal deliveries if it can deal with its problems and then demonstrate this to the House.</p>","source":"Cov","page":22,"indexKey":"unsafe","review_status":"reviewed","reviewer":"lichen","type":"covenantExternalRelations","impact":{"value":"minor"},"hidden":false,"tainted":false},"effects":[],"flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"12.343","systemId":"arm5e","systemVersion":"2.4.0.4","createdTime":1749287868926,"modifiedTime":1749370310399,"lastModifiedBy":"xMd6zrGNn4dbQYey"},"_id":"bgLRF6ZKPsvywmqe","sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J":3}}
{"folder":"g2kV0ETU5Ech2O66","name":"Guild","type":"flaw","img":"systems/arm5e/assets/icons/base-magic.svg","system":{"description":"<p>The covenfolk have a political organization that can arrange for many of them to withdraw their services simultaneously. The guild usually strikes only when it feels its members suffer mistreatment. The guild agitates for better wages, shorter hours, and less dangerous working conditions. Many guilds also provide funds for medical help, retirement, funerals, the widows of members, and other social services.</p>","source":"Cov","page":19,"indexKey":"guild","review_status":"reviewed","reviewer":"lichen","type":"covenantResidents","impact":{"value":"minor"},"hidden":false,"tainted":false},"effects":[],"flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"12.343","systemId":"arm5e","systemVersion":"2.4.0.4","createdTime":1749287883937,"modifiedTime":1749370310406,"lastModifiedBy":"xMd6zrGNn4dbQYey"},"_id":"cEOHdpnpc03W1YKl","sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J":3}}
{"folder":"BENb4deddxRJwwcu","name":"Urban","type":"flaw","img":"systems/arm5e/assets/icons/base-magic.svg","system":{"description":"<p>The covenant is in a small market town. Many of the inhabitants are not part of the covenant, and the covenant does not rule the town. </p><p>Many Spring covenants in cities lack a Magical aura, and should take the Missing Aura Hook. Older covenants usually have an aura, because they have workspaces out in the countries, have a regio that contains their laboratories, or have created caverns deep below the city where an aura has grown up due to their magical practices.</p>","source":"Cov","page":11,"indexKey":"urban","review_status":"reviewed","reviewer":"lichen","type":"covenantSite","impact":{"value":"minor"},"hidden":false,"tainted":false},"effects":[],"flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"12.343","systemId":"arm5e","systemVersion":"2.4.0.4","createdTime":1749287885314,"modifiedTime":1749370310412,"lastModifiedBy":"xMd6zrGNn4dbQYey"},"_id":"dY1UrTIMJaHYQCgS","sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J":3}}
{"folder":"egD6BYeMAt02SJl1","name":"Crumbling","type":"flaw","img":"systems/arm5e/assets/icons/base-magic.svg","system":{"description":"<p>Many mundane castles are in disrepair. Their function is to defend places in times of strife, and when their owners believe an extended period of peace has arrived, they do not perform necessary maintenance. Some castles are simply badly made. For example, there are many motte and bailey castles which have had their wooden motte tower replaced with a stone one. As these compact the artificial mound upon which they sit, they develop enormous cracks, and eventually fall to pieces. Crumbling is a useful Hook for saga with Gothic themes.</p>","source":"Cov","page":15,"indexKey":"crumbling","review_status":"reviewed","reviewer":"lichen","type":"other","impact":{"value":"minor"},"hidden":false,"tainted":false},"effects":[],"flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"12.343","systemId":"arm5e","systemVersion":"2.4.0.4","createdTime":1749287871166,"modifiedTime":1749370310419,"lastModifiedBy":"xMd6zrGNn4dbQYey"},"_id":"eH2Dr8fnbuueqd4B","sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J":3}}
{"folder":"0tTkM6zxVjQTvaf8","name":"Centralized Kingdom","type":"flaw","img":"systems/arm5e/assets/icons/base-magic.svg","system":{"description":"<p>In some parts of Europe, England for example, it is perfectly clear who owns every bit of land. A newly founded covenant in such an area will need to explain its presence to, and come to terms with, its putative noble lord.</p>","source":"Cov","page":22,"indexKey":"centralized-kingdom","review_status":"reviewed","reviewer":"lichen","type":"covenantExternalRelations","impact":{"value":"minor"},"hidden":false,"tainted":false},"effects":[],"flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"12.343","systemId":"arm5e","systemVersion":"2.4.0.4","createdTime":1749287868926,"modifiedTime":1749370310426,"lastModifiedBy":"xMd6zrGNn4dbQYey"},"_id":"eeBfzw23wEGnWKFe","sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J":3}}
{"folder":"BENb4deddxRJwwcu","name":"Weak Aura","type":"flaw","img":"systems/arm5e/assets/icons/base-magic.svg","system":{"description":"<p>Subtract one point from the covenant’s Magic aura. Most young magi would not wish to settle in an area with a poor aura, so each should consider the story potential of their reasons for settling such a substandard site.</p>","source":"Cov","page":11,"indexKey":"weak-aura","review_status":"reviewed","reviewer":"lichen","type":"covenantSite","impact":{"value":"minor"},"hidden":false,"tainted":false},"effects":[],"flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"12.343","systemId":"arm5e","systemVersion":"2.4.0.4","createdTime":1749287885314,"modifiedTime":1749370310432,"lastModifiedBy":"xMd6zrGNn4dbQYey"},"_id":"eeOOB6jOoK7ttzw8","sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J":3}}
{"folder":"0tTkM6zxVjQTvaf8","name":"Infamous","type":"flaw","img":"systems/arm5e/assets/icons/base-magic.svg","system":{"description":"<p>The covenant is mistrusted, has a checkered Hermetic record, or is held in contempt. This mirrors the Prestigious Minor Boon.</p>","source":"Cov","page":22,"indexKey":"infamous","review_status":"reviewed","reviewer":"lichen","type":"covenantExternalRelations","impact":{"value":"minor"},"hidden":false,"tainted":false},"effects":[],"flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"12.343","systemId":"arm5e","systemVersion":"2.4.0.4","createdTime":1749287868926,"modifiedTime":1749370310439,"lastModifiedBy":"xMd6zrGNn4dbQYey"},"_id":"fAMdQjTe7cLynASP","sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J":3}}
{"folder":"0tTkM6zxVjQTvaf8","name":"Itinerants","type":"flaw","img":"systems/arm5e/assets/icons/base-magic.svg","system":{"description":"<p>A mobile community visits the covenant every year. This might be a wandering group of minstrels, a family of merchants with their servants, or bands of farm laborers looking for work. Some covenfolk welcome these arrivals, with their news and money, while others find them a source of endless trouble. While they may pick fights and engage in petty theft, they also carry rumors, trade goods, and money.</p>","source":"Cov","page":22,"indexKey":"itinerants","review_status":"reviewed","reviewer":"lichen","type":"covenantExternalRelations","impact":{"value":"minor"},"hidden":false,"tainted":false},"effects":[],"flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"12.343","systemId":"arm5e","systemVersion":"2.4.0.4","createdTime":1749287868926,"modifiedTime":1749370310445,"lastModifiedBy":"xMd6zrGNn4dbQYey"},"_id":"fKSIV3u9wUK74Fqf","sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J":3}}
{"folder":"FvLHeGVEQh6UL4Jd","name":"Missing Aura","type":"flaw","img":"systems/arm5e/assets/icons/base-magic.svg","system":{"description":"<p>The characters have settled in an area where they lack the most fundamental tool required to study their Art, a magical aura. Stories focus on how they better their situation, and how the covenant remains together when there is such a strong temptation for some magi to leave. </p><p>Marco, widely considered a charlatan, claims to have met a faerie king who held the aura of the fallen Covenant of the Redbreasted Warriors in a wine bottle. He said that he would invite to dinner any magus who could meet his five challenges, and allow them to choose their menu from his entire demesne, including, presumably, the bottle. Marco, cowardly, refused to meet his challenges and, fed only on pea gruel and water, fled the king’s hall by night.</p>","source":"Cov","page":9,"indexKey":"missing-aura","review_status":"reviewed","reviewer":"lichen","type":"covenantSite","impact":{"value":"major"},"hidden":false,"tainted":false},"effects":[],"flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"12.343","systemId":"arm5e","systemVersion":"2.4.0.4","createdTime":1749287885314,"modifiedTime":1749370310451,"lastModifiedBy":"xMd6zrGNn4dbQYey"},"_id":"fzIyThPogI0sozPW","sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J":3}}
{"folder":"g2kV0ETU5Ech2O66","name":"Indigenes","type":"flaw","img":"systems/arm5e/assets/icons/base-magic.svg","system":{"description":"<p>The covenant was founded through a colonial process when the magi and their primary servants took possession of an area occupied by another people. The covenant’s population is stratified: the new arrivals rule, the indigenous population serve. The covenant would be far more stable, in the long term, if the two groups could reconcile, and perhaps form a hybrid culture, but that is difficult. The indigenous population feels generally angry and vengeful. The incoming population, on the other hand, feels generally superior and is subject to the temptations that the conqueror feels in their treatment of the conquered.</p>","source":"Cov","page":20,"indexKey":"indigenes","review_status":"reviewed","reviewer":"lichen","type":"covenantResidents","impact":{"value":"minor"},"hidden":false,"tainted":false},"effects":[],"flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"12.343","systemId":"arm5e","systemVersion":"2.4.0.4","createdTime":1749287883937,"modifiedTime":1749370310458,"lastModifiedBy":"xMd6zrGNn4dbQYey"},"_id":"g0MLYUYcBU2cVi8B","sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J":3}}
{"folder":"BENb4deddxRJwwcu","name":"Resident Nuisance","type":"flaw","img":"systems/arm5e/assets/icons/base-magic.svg","system":{"description":"<p>A minor mystical creature, or group of creatures, resides in the covenant. Their activities are no more harmful than minor vandalism, but cause waste, expense, and arguments. The magi could defeat and destroy these creatures, but it would take time and effort better directed elsewhere. This Hook may be Unknown. </p><p>A Redcap named Marco, who has been unable to locate his trousers on several occasions, reports that in one covenant, the grogs claim that a maiden appears to them in the depth of the night watch, carrying a mug of hot toddy. When they drink it, they fall unconscious, and are usually found naked in a barn. The magi have tried to hunt this faerie, but the grogs have proved almost entirely unhelpful. The ruler of the covenant believes the maiden is actually a prank played by generations of apprentices, abused by slothful grogs.</p>","source":"Cov","page":10,"indexKey":"resident-nuisance","review_status":"reviewed","reviewer":"lichen","type":"covenantSite","impact":{"value":"minor"},"hidden":false,"tainted":false},"effects":[],"flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"12.343","systemId":"arm5e","systemVersion":"2.4.0.4","createdTime":1749287885314,"modifiedTime":1749370310464,"lastModifiedBy":"xMd6zrGNn4dbQYey"},"_id":"gIUuF3irYjvP0dYZ","sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J":3}}
{"folder":"g2kV0ETU5Ech2O66","name":"Refugee","type":"flaw","img":"systems/arm5e/assets/icons/base-magic.svg","system":{"description":"<p>A displaced nobleman, or noblewoman, has come to the covenant seeking shelter from the forces of a usurp- er who has stolen his or her land and riches. The refugee has useful skills, and may aid the magi, but intends to eventually seek revenge and restoration. This Hook may be Unknown.</p>","source":"Cov","page":20,"indexKey":"refugee","review_status":"reviewed","reviewer":"lichen","type":"covenantResidents","impact":{"value":"minor"},"hidden":false,"tainted":false},"effects":[],"flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"12.343","systemId":"arm5e","systemVersion":"2.4.0.4","createdTime":1749287883937,"modifiedTime":1749370310474,"lastModifiedBy":"xMd6zrGNn4dbQYey"},"_id":"gmKOPCaRcCaLjRU5","sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J":3}}
{"folder":"g2kV0ETU5Ech2O66","name":"Rights and Customs","type":"flaw","img":"systems/arm5e/assets/icons/base-magic.svg","system":{"description":"<p>Members of the covenant have a series of traditional rights that cause the magi difficulty, but cannot be altered without serious damage to covenant morale. These include local holidays, mandatory feasts, exemption from death taxes, and other odd local customs.</p>","source":"Cov","page":20,"indexKey":"rights-and-customs","review_status":"reviewed","reviewer":"lichen","type":"covenantResidents","impact":{"value":"minor"},"hidden":false,"tainted":false},"effects":[],"flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"12.343","systemId":"arm5e","systemVersion":"2.4.0.4","createdTime":1749287883937,"modifiedTime":1749370310480,"lastModifiedBy":"xMd6zrGNn4dbQYey"},"_id":"hqjXsiAOEk6IiJm5","sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J":3}}
{"folder":"O5LhN2J2Ed3J2OWc","name":"Chapter House","type":"flaw","img":"systems/arm5e/assets/icons/base-magic.svg","system":{"description":"<p>The covenant owns and controls a second, smaller site, far from the covenant’s main holding. The site is so valuable that a small, dependent covenant, called a chapter house, has been founded there. Chapter houses tend to agitate for independence from their motherhouses, but deft handling allows them to act as efficient harvesters of material that rivals would otherwise claim.</p>","source":"Cov","page":19,"indexKey":"chapter-house","review_status":"reviewed","reviewer":"lichen","type":"covenantResidents","impact":{"value":"major"},"hidden":false,"tainted":false},"effects":[],"flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"12.343","systemId":"arm5e","systemVersion":"2.4.0.4","createdTime":1749287883937,"modifiedTime":1749370310487,"lastModifiedBy":"xMd6zrGNn4dbQYey"},"_id":"iCXNlgKBEF90526a","sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J":3}}
{"folder":"0tTkM6zxVjQTvaf8","name":"Unsubtle Predecessor","type":"flaw","img":"systems/arm5e/assets/icons/base-magic.svg","system":{"description":"<p>One of the covenant’s founders funded its early work by pretending that the covenant had a gold mine or similarly enviable source of portable wealth. The covenant has claimed, for many years, that things have changed and they no longer have unending reserves of this commodity, but many local nobles do not believe them, or believe that they have maintained a sizable treasury of the stuff.</p>","source":"Cov","page":22,"indexKey":"unsubtle-predecessor","review_status":"reviewed","reviewer":"lichen","type":"covenantExternalRelations","impact":{"value":"minor"},"hidden":false,"tainted":false},"effects":[],"flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"12.343","systemId":"arm5e","systemVersion":"2.4.0.4","createdTime":1749287868926,"modifiedTime":1749370310493,"lastModifiedBy":"xMd6zrGNn4dbQYey"},"_id":"ib4VDU21Qjs1IcG4","sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J":3}}
{"folder":"BENb4deddxRJwwcu","name":"Uncontrolled Portal","type":"flaw","img":"systems/arm5e/assets/icons/base-magic.svg","system":{"description":"<p>As per the “Mystical Portal” Boon, except that the portal is not under the covenant’s control. This Hook may be Unknown. </p><p>Many covenants have a portal that they do not control, but the harried magi near Granada certainly have the largest. The Pillars of Hercules, the islands that stand at the western edge of the known world, are thought to contain gateways to Arcadia and the Magical realm. This would explain why all manner of odd things dwell there. The magi of Granada have set themselves a task: to monitor the gate for creatures that might harm Europe. They are attempting to have a Tribunal recognize them as a dedicated covenant — see the Boon of the same name — but many magi point out that Granada has every reason to monitor the portal regardless of support.</p>","source":"Cov","page":11,"indexKey":"uncontrolled-portal","review_status":"reviewed","reviewer":"lichen","type":"covenantSite","impact":{"value":"minor"},"hidden":false,"tainted":false},"effects":[],"flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"12.343","systemId":"arm5e","systemVersion":"2.4.0.4","createdTime":1749287885314,"modifiedTime":1749370310498,"lastModifiedBy":"xMd6zrGNn4dbQYey"},"_id":"j5J9hZgRYoFtFcHB","sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J":3}}
{"folder":"r7IGd9SqC2sfaO6M","name":"Monastery","type":"flaw","img":"systems/arm5e/assets/icons/base-magic.svg","system":{"description":"<p>There is a monastery near the covenant, which uses much of the local land to support its monks. The monastery is not militarized, but the local population finds its leaders persuasive, and as it grows, it may desire some of the covenant’s land. Even now, it expects financial support from the covenant.</p>","source":"Cov","page":25,"indexKey":"monastery","review_status":"reviewed","reviewer":"lichen","type":"covenantSurroundings","impact":{"value":"minor"},"hidden":false,"tainted":false},"effects":[],"flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"12.343","systemId":"arm5e","systemVersion":"2.4.0.4","createdTime":1749287886938,"modifiedTime":1749370310506,"lastModifiedBy":"xMd6zrGNn4dbQYey"},"_id":"jyzdvtuta5BGEqaW","sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J":3}}
{"folder":"r7IGd9SqC2sfaO6M","name":"Ungarrisoned Castle","type":"flaw","img":"systems/arm5e/assets/icons/base-magic.svg","system":{"description":"<p>Within the covenant’s vicinity lies a castle belonging to a major noble or the Crown. Like most castles, it is ungarrisoned in times of peace. A constable, perhaps a minor knight, and his household keep it ready for rapid militarization, should trouble brew.</p>","source":"Cov","page":25,"indexKey":"ungarrisoned-castle","review_status":"reviewed","reviewer":"lichen","type":"covenantSurroundings","impact":{"value":"minor"},"hidden":false,"tainted":false},"effects":[],"flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"12.343","systemId":"arm5e","systemVersion":"2.4.0.4","createdTime":1749287886938,"modifiedTime":1749370310512,"lastModifiedBy":"xMd6zrGNn4dbQYey"},"_id":"k1i8ITrmKjnABNhA","sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J":3}}
{"folder":"0tTkM6zxVjQTvaf8","name":"Hermetic Politics","type":"flaw","img":"systems/arm5e/assets/icons/base-magic.svg","system":{"description":"<p>The covenant is engaged in the elaborate game of trading of favors that passes for politics in some Hermetic Tribunals. When the saga begins, the covenant owes favors to three other covenants, but is owed three favors as well.</p>","source":"Cov","page":22,"indexKey":"hermetic-politics","review_status":"reviewed","reviewer":"lichen","type":"covenantExternalRelations","impact":{"value":"minor"},"hidden":false,"tainted":false},"effects":[],"flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"12.343","systemId":"arm5e","systemVersion":"2.4.0.4","createdTime":1749287868926,"modifiedTime":1749370310519,"lastModifiedBy":"xMd6zrGNn4dbQYey"},"_id":"k1vu3b27bXUeaVxQ","sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J":3}}
{"folder":"O5LhN2J2Ed3J2OWc","name":"Diabolic Corruption","type":"flaw","img":"systems/arm5e/assets/icons/base-magic.svg","system":{"description":"<p>Some of the covenfolk are diabolists. This is difficult to detect because the demon they serve has clouded their minds, so that they look normal when scryed upon, even forgetting briefly their Infernal servitude. They have invited their master and his minions into the covenant with depraved Infernal rites, so the Aegis does not bar them, although it does limit their supernatural abilities.</p>","source":"Cov","page":19,"indexKey":"diabolic-corruption","review_status":"reviewed","reviewer":"lichen","type":"covenantResidents","impact":{"value":"major"},"hidden":false,"tainted":false},"effects":[],"flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"12.343","systemId":"arm5e","systemVersion":"2.4.0.4","createdTime":1749287883937,"modifiedTime":1749370310525,"lastModifiedBy":"xMd6zrGNn4dbQYey"},"_id":"kJ5nfO9NfUTxtJRf","sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J":3}}
{"folder":"egD6BYeMAt02SJl1","name":"Outbuildings","type":"flaw","img":"systems/arm5e/assets/icons/base-magic.svg","system":{"description":"<p>Small hamlets often rise around castles. These house the lesser servants of the castle’s owners, those who provide goods for these servants, and those servants whose work is noxious, like tanners. These hamlets, if too close to the castle, provide cover and resources for besieging forces. Some castles’ lords destroy encroaching buildings, while others eventually throw a wall about them, creating a fortified village. Your covenant has yet to embrace either option.</p>","source":"Cov","page":15,"indexKey":"outbuildings","review_status":"reviewed","reviewer":"lichen","type":"other","impact":{"value":"minor"},"hidden":false,"tainted":false},"effects":[],"flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"12.343","systemId":"arm5e","systemVersion":"2.4.0.4","createdTime":1749287871166,"modifiedTime":1749370310530,"lastModifiedBy":"xMd6zrGNn4dbQYey"},"_id":"kiUEaNqSEMra8k2W","sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J":3}}
{"folder":"g2kV0ETU5Ech2O66","name":"Spies","type":"flaw","img":"systems/arm5e/assets/icons/base-magic.svg","system":{"description":"<p>Agents of a rival have infiltrated the covenant or a nearby town. They are content to simply collect information at this time, but might perform sabotage as the rival’s scheme develops. This Hook may be Unknown.</p>","source":"Cov","page":20,"indexKey":"spies","review_status":"reviewed","reviewer":"lichen","type":"covenantResidents","impact":{"value":"minor"},"hidden":false,"tainted":false},"effects":[],"flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"12.343","systemId":"arm5e","systemVersion":"2.4.0.4","createdTime":1749287883937,"modifiedTime":1749370310540,"lastModifiedBy":"xMd6zrGNn4dbQYey"},"_id":"lrAPpoY961olmiiQ","sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J":3}}
{"folder":"BENb4deddxRJwwcu","name":"Regio with Unexpected Entries","type":"flaw","img":"systems/arm5e/assets/icons/base-magic.svg","system":{"description":"<p>The covenant is located in a magical regio, but it can be entered in many ways. The covenfolk remain unaware of many of these, discovering them only when an unfortunate person or creature stumbles upon the covenant. This Hook may be Unknown. </p><p>The Dogrose School is particularly notorious for the ease with which it can be found. The School hides behind a city, and draws Gifted children to itself, by possessing their toys with an urge to sneak out on moonlit nights and walk odd streets, drawing their little masters away. House Bonisagus long ago claimed the Dogrose School for its own. Its members teach the little pupils Latin and a bit of Magic Theory before sending them to other masters. Sometimes the toys bring other, more difficult, visitors.</p>","source":"Cov","page":10,"indexKey":"regio-with-unexpected-entries","review_status":"reviewed","reviewer":"lichen","type":"covenantSite","impact":{"value":"minor"},"hidden":false,"tainted":false},"effects":[],"flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"12.343","systemId":"arm5e","systemVersion":"2.4.0.4","createdTime":1749287885314,"modifiedTime":1749370310546,"lastModifiedBy":"xMd6zrGNn4dbQYey"},"_id":"lrIV8UtPufcXYk1R","sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J":3}}
{"folder":"O5LhN2J2Ed3J2OWc","name":"Divided Loyalty","type":"flaw","img":"systems/arm5e/assets/icons/base-magic.svg","system":{"description":"<p>The covenant is divided into factions, and the Prevailing Loyalty is calculated separately for each faction. These factions may be professional, political, or personal, but they are in competition with each other. Actions that affect the loyalty points (see Chapter 3: Governance) of the covenant as a whole affect all factions. Actions which benefit the loyalty of one faction over the others will cause a decrease in loyalty of the other factions equal to one half of the loyalty points gained. If the gap in Prevailing Loyalty between factions ever reaches 3 or more points, then a story results based on the tensions between the factions. This Hook is compatible with other Residents Boons and Hooks that affect loyalty; work out the total loyalty points, then divide them between the factions — but not necessarily equally.</p>","source":"Cov","page":19,"indexKey":"divided-loyalty","review_status":"reviewed","reviewer":"lichen","type":"covenantResidents","impact":{"value":"major"},"hidden":false,"tainted":false},"effects":[],"flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"12.343","systemId":"arm5e","systemVersion":"2.4.0.4","createdTime":1749287883937,"modifiedTime":1749370310552,"lastModifiedBy":"xMd6zrGNn4dbQYey"},"_id":"meCXxonSdSrOE2MQ","sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J":3}}
{"folder":"r7IGd9SqC2sfaO6M","name":"Monster","type":"flaw","img":"systems/arm5e/assets/icons/base-magic.svg","system":{"description":"<p>A powerful mystical creature lives near the covenant. The creature can be aligned with any realm, and should be too powerful for the player characters to defeat at the beginning of the saga. This Hook may be Unknown.</p>","source":"Cov","page":25,"indexKey":"monster","review_status":"reviewed","reviewer":"lichen","type":"covenantSurroundings","impact":{"value":"minor"},"hidden":false,"tainted":false},"effects":[],"flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"12.343","systemId":"arm5e","systemVersion":"2.4.0.4","createdTime":1749287886938,"modifiedTime":1749370310558,"lastModifiedBy":"xMd6zrGNn4dbQYey"},"_id":"n62xQQV2yxmfKlz1","sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J":3}}
{"folder":"0tTkM6zxVjQTvaf8","name":"Rival","type":"flaw","img":"systems/arm5e/assets/icons/base-magic.svg","system":{"description":"<p>Someone or some group is working to undermine or stymie the covenant. This rival may be much weaker than the covenant, as long as he is capable of causing problems worthy of stories. This Hook may be Unknown.</p>","source":"Cov","page":22,"indexKey":"rival","review_status":"reviewed","reviewer":"lichen","type":"covenantExternalRelations","impact":{"value":"minor"},"hidden":false,"tainted":false},"effects":[],"flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"12.343","systemId":"arm5e","systemVersion":"2.4.0.4","createdTime":1749287868926,"modifiedTime":1749370310563,"lastModifiedBy":"xMd6zrGNn4dbQYey"},"_id":"nUVGMT5c6XQKS6nm","sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J":3}}
{"folder":"FvLHeGVEQh6UL4Jd","name":"Regio","type":"flaw","img":"systems/arm5e/assets/icons/base-magic.svg","system":{"description":"<p>There is a regio on the covenant site, although the covenant is not in it. The regio has inhabitants who occasionally come out and cause problems. This Hook may be Unknown. If the regio is not magical, that counts as an additional Minor Hook. </p><p>A convoluted Wizard’s War once arose from such a regio. Knowing it to be full of untamed sprites, a magus encircled the regio with a trellis of roses, grown thick then turned to iron. It was the nature of the regio to send forth the secret desires of members of the covenant, and so the childhood love of another magus, or a faerie of her shape, was killed upon the thorns. The second magus did not declare war because his love had died. Rather, he did so because he believed that the death of the one he loved most was what the first magus most desired, and that the regio had granted it to him.</p>","source":"Cov","page":9,"indexKey":"regio","review_status":"reviewed","reviewer":"lichen","type":"covenantSite","impact":{"value":"major"},"hidden":false,"tainted":false},"effects":[],"flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"12.343","systemId":"arm5e","systemVersion":"2.4.0.4","createdTime":1749287885314,"modifiedTime":1749370310571,"lastModifiedBy":"xMd6zrGNn4dbQYey"},"_id":"oLgTODWuQt2wYGQA","sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J":3}}
{"folder":"BENb4deddxRJwwcu","name":"Haunted","type":"flaw","img":"systems/arm5e/assets/icons/base-magic.svg","system":{"description":"<p>Ghosts, perhaps of former magi, haunt the covenant. Most ghosts want to finish their worldly business before they pass away. The magi may wish to assist them. This Hook may be Unknown.</p>","source":"Cov","page":10,"indexKey":"haunted","review_status":"reviewed","reviewer":"lichen","type":"covenantSite","impact":{"value":"minor"},"hidden":false,"tainted":false},"effects":[],"flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"12.343","systemId":"arm5e","systemVersion":"2.4.0.4","createdTime":1749287885314,"modifiedTime":1749370310576,"lastModifiedBy":"xMd6zrGNn4dbQYey"},"_id":"ohxoca8QflohlpcW","sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J":3}}
{"folder":"0tTkM6zxVjQTvaf8","name":"Ancestral Error","type":"flaw","img":"systems/arm5e/assets/icons/base-magic.svg","system":{"description":"<p>One of the magi who founded the covenant made a grave error that harmed many people, or willingly performed a deeply sinful act. The covenant must eventually face the consequences of this mistake. This Hook may be Unknown.</p>","source":"Cov","page":22,"indexKey":"ancestral-error","review_status":"reviewed","reviewer":"lichen","type":"covenantExternalRelations","impact":{"value":"minor"},"hidden":false,"tainted":false},"effects":[],"flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"12.343","systemId":"arm5e","systemVersion":"2.4.0.4","createdTime":1749287868926,"modifiedTime":1749370310582,"lastModifiedBy":"xMd6zrGNn4dbQYey"},"_id":"qT6OTfd4cNcqNSLg","sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J":3}}
{"folder":"FvLHeGVEQh6UL4Jd","name":"Road","type":"flaw","img":"systems/arm5e/assets/icons/base-magic.svg","system":{"description":"<p>The covenant is on an important mystical trail of some kind, so that mystical creatures, from one or more realms, often turn up at the covenant. </p><p>A most unfortunate covenant lies near the Chapel That Cannot Sleep. The chapel lies on an ancient battlefield, and was raised on the dun that surmounted the fallen. A mythic road, a right of way, sometimes appears when the corpse of a murdered man is carried to a graveyard, and in this case as each body was carried to the site, it created a road. A vast number of roads now leads to the Chapel, stretching out for miles in the direction of the pursuit of the foot soldiers of the losing side. All manner of metaphysical detritus washes up at the Chapel, and disturbs the sleeping dead.</p>","source":"Cov","page":9,"indexKey":"road","review_status":"reviewed","reviewer":"lichen","type":"covenantSite","impact":{"value":"major"},"hidden":false,"tainted":false},"effects":[],"flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"12.343","systemId":"arm5e","systemVersion":"2.4.0.4","createdTime":1749287885314,"modifiedTime":1749370310590,"lastModifiedBy":"xMd6zrGNn4dbQYey"},"_id":"rOoTOj14jDltiTzx","sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J":3}}
{"folder":"BENb4deddxRJwwcu","name":"Erratically Mobile","type":"flaw","img":"systems/arm5e/assets/icons/base-magic.svg","system":{"description":"<p>This covenant regularly moves, but its movements are erratic, and are interspersed with periods where the covenant settles in an area for a season. An example is a covenant of magi who have decided to follow the trade roads into Asia, traveling during summer and staying in major cities each winter. They have no name for themselves and lack any common property other than the coffee pot they bought in Aleppo from a Redcap who happened to pass by and learn their story.</p>","source":"Cov","page":10,"indexKey":"erratically-mobile","review_status":"reviewed","reviewer":"lichen","type":"covenantSite","impact":{"value":"minor"},"hidden":false,"tainted":false},"effects":[],"flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"12.343","systemId":"arm5e","systemVersion":"2.4.0.4","createdTime":1749287885314,"modifiedTime":1749370310595,"lastModifiedBy":"xMd6zrGNn4dbQYey"},"_id":"rkIi6nw9xXUYVsL1","sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J":3}}
{"folder":"0tTkM6zxVjQTvaf8","name":"House Covenant","type":"flaw","img":"systems/arm5e/assets/icons/base-magic.svg","system":{"description":"<p>A single House rules this covenant; the other magi who live in it are its servants. The leaders of the House appoint the leaders of the covenant, and the covenant’s charter forbids local magi from assuming greater control.</p>","source":"Cov","page":22,"indexKey":"house-covenant","review_status":"reviewed","reviewer":"lichen","type":"covenantExternalRelations","impact":{"value":"minor"},"hidden":false,"tainted":false},"effects":[],"flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"12.343","systemId":"arm5e","systemVersion":"2.4.0.4","createdTime":1749287868926,"modifiedTime":1749370310602,"lastModifiedBy":"xMd6zrGNn4dbQYey"},"_id":"rpLTCkxEHmUIKnPy","sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J":3}}
{"folder":"g2kV0ETU5Ech2O66","name":"Alienable Land","type":"flaw","img":"systems/arm5e/assets/icons/base-magic.svg","system":{"description":"<p>The covenant allows its people to own farmland, homes, and shops, rather than renting them. This allows industry to develop more quickly, as residents have a reason to improve their dwellings and land. This also allows covenfolk to mortgage their land, to secure the money required to start or expand their businesses. Stories arise when the land is sold, or lost, to creditors who come from outside the covenant. These heirs are unused to the covenant’s customs, and might seek the aid of a higher authority to recover property they consider theirs by right. Many covenants, for example, allow female heirs to inherit far better portions than outsiders might expect, or local laws might allow.</p>","source":"Cov","page":19,"indexKey":"alienable-land","review_status":"reviewed","reviewer":"lichen","type":"covenantResidents","impact":{"value":"minor"},"hidden":false,"tainted":false},"effects":[],"flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"12.343","systemId":"arm5e","systemVersion":"2.4.0.4","createdTime":1749287883937,"modifiedTime":1749370310608,"lastModifiedBy":"xMd6zrGNn4dbQYey"},"_id":"s6VbV76wc0kpf2F7","sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J":3}}
{"folder":"of6RVKST8vt4Wki1","name":"Ruined Covenant","type":"flaw","img":"systems/arm5e/assets/icons/base-magic.svg","system":{"description":"<p>The covenant is near the site of a powerful covenant, which has fallen into ruin. The younger covenant controls some of the previous covenant’s resources, but has not discovered them all, nor explored the central site of its predecessor.</p>","source":"Cov","page":24,"indexKey":"ruined-covenant","review_status":"reviewed","reviewer":"lichen","type":"covenantSurroundings","impact":{"value":"major"},"hidden":false,"tainted":false},"effects":[],"flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"12.343","systemId":"arm5e","systemVersion":"2.4.0.4","createdTime":1749287886938,"modifiedTime":1749370310614,"lastModifiedBy":"xMd6zrGNn4dbQYey"},"_id":"tbB7GWlsKOmu0H4K","sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J":3}}
{"folder":"BENb4deddxRJwwcu","name":"Road","type":"flaw","img":"systems/arm5e/assets/icons/base-magic.svg","system":{"description":"<p>The covenant is on an important mundane road, river, or sea route, so that people often turn up at the covenant, bringing or causing stories.</p>","source":"Cov","page":11,"indexKey":"road","review_status":"reviewed","reviewer":"lichen","type":"covenantSite","impact":{"value":"minor"},"hidden":false,"tainted":false},"effects":[],"flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"12.343","systemId":"arm5e","systemVersion":"2.4.0.4","createdTime":1749287885314,"modifiedTime":1749370310622,"lastModifiedBy":"xMd6zrGNn4dbQYey"},"_id":"tq36m9qy9e54tuNI","sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J":3}}
{"folder":"g2kV0ETU5Ech2O66","name":"Dumping Ground","type":"flaw","img":"systems/arm5e/assets/icons/base-magic.svg","system":{"description":"<p>Many minor nobles have their older relatives retire to the covenant, in exchange for political favors and payments. In some areas it is traditional, if unseemly, for sons to force their fathers into monasteries, allowing the son to inherit before the father’s death and have the father’s upkeep paid out of monastic coffers. Covenants are not generally so generous, but some — particularly those influenced by House Jerbiton — accept aged, usually mentally impaired, relatives of noblemen, who are nursed in their final years away from their homes. Intellectually impaired children are also sometimes given to covenants, under a stipend system.</p>","source":"Cov","page":19,"indexKey":"dumping-ground","review_status":"reviewed","reviewer":"lichen","type":"covenantResidents","impact":{"value":"minor"},"hidden":false,"tainted":false},"effects":[],"flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"12.343","systemId":"arm5e","systemVersion":"2.4.0.4","createdTime":1749287883937,"modifiedTime":1749370310628,"lastModifiedBy":"xMd6zrGNn4dbQYey"},"_id":"uEBmSTGX4tfWqnLg","sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J":3}}
{"folder":"k0vela35v1xs3g2S","name":"Hedge Tradition","type":"flaw","img":"systems/arm5e/assets/icons/base-magic.svg","system":{"description":"<p>The area in which the covenant lies is outside the usual sphere of Hermetic influence. It lies within the established territory of one of the hedge traditions that is active on the borders of the Order. Some members of the hedge tradition resent the covenant’s presence and its use of resources that they believe are rightfully theirs, but there is no formal state of war, yet.</p>","source":"Cov","page":21,"indexKey":"hedge-tradition","review_status":"reviewed","reviewer":"lichen","type":"covenantExternalRelations","impact":{"value":"major"},"hidden":false,"tainted":false},"effects":[],"flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"12.343","systemId":"arm5e","systemVersion":"2.4.0.4","createdTime":1749287868926,"modifiedTime":1749370310633,"lastModifiedBy":"xMd6zrGNn4dbQYey"},"_id":"vWSE5ZSo6UBq8oQS","sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J":3}}
{"folder":"r7IGd9SqC2sfaO6M","name":"Ford","type":"flaw","img":"systems/arm5e/assets/icons/base-magic.svg","system":{"description":"<p>Near the covenant lies a ford that is the most convenient river-crossing for at least three days travel in either direction. The river channels travelers to the ford, which can be exploited for income, but the ford is also an obvious military objective in times of strife, since it can be held by few men against many.</p>","source":"Cov","page":24,"indexKey":"ford","review_status":"reviewed","reviewer":"lichen","type":"covenantSurroundings","impact":{"value":"minor"},"hidden":false,"tainted":false},"effects":[],"flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"12.343","systemId":"arm5e","systemVersion":"2.4.0.4","createdTime":1749287886938,"modifiedTime":1749370310642,"lastModifiedBy":"xMd6zrGNn4dbQYey"},"_id":"vhBb4YEbqILYO2Bd","sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J":3}}
{"folder":"k0vela35v1xs3g2S","name":"Hermetic Services","type":"flaw","img":"systems/arm5e/assets/icons/base-magic.svg","system":{"description":"<p>A handful of covenants survive by providing resources to other covenants. These resources include goods, like special inks and vis, and services, like creating longevity effects. These covenants are particularly dependent on Hermetic peace for their prosperity, which forces them to act as conciliators in difficult situations.</p>","source":"Cov","page":21,"indexKey":"hermetic-services","review_status":"reviewed","reviewer":"LICHEN","type":"covenantExternalRelations","impact":{"value":"major"},"hidden":false,"tainted":false},"effects":[],"flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"12.343","systemId":"arm5e","systemVersion":"2.4.0.4","createdTime":1749287868926,"modifiedTime":1749370310647,"lastModifiedBy":"xMd6zrGNn4dbQYey"},"_id":"wpfQkEIxQpBtVW6Z","sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J":3}}
{"folder":"BENb4deddxRJwwcu","name":"Poorly Defensible","type":"flaw","img":"systems/arm5e/assets/icons/base-magic.svg","system":{"description":"<p>The covenant’s founders placed it in a site that is overlooked by a cliff, can be flooded by diverting a river, or is otherwise not suited to a conventional siege defense. The magi need to retain good relations with their neighbors, at least until they remedy their defenses. </p><p>There is a covenant that made a deal with a nobleman in which they provided him with a longevity ritual, and in exchange, he granted them six acres of land. The cunning nobleman gave the covenant a lengthy strip of rocky beach. Stubborn and unwilling to allow themselves to be shamed, the magi reclaimed sixty hectares of land, surrounding it with a massive dike. The people within the dike are fatalistic, and each family keeps a rowboat in the roof cavity of their house. Most male children are named Noah, for luck.</p>","source":"Cov","page":10,"indexKey":"poorly-defensible","review_status":"reviewed","reviewer":"lichen","type":"covenantSite","impact":{"value":"minor"},"hidden":false,"tainted":false},"effects":[],"flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"12.343","systemId":"arm5e","systemVersion":"2.4.0.4","createdTime":1749287885314,"modifiedTime":1749370310653,"lastModifiedBy":"xMd6zrGNn4dbQYey"},"_id":"x88auhPUkGaDDRvZ","sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J":3}}
{"folder":"k0vela35v1xs3g2S","name":"Ceremonies","type":"flaw","img":"systems/arm5e/assets/icons/base-magic.svg","system":{"description":"<p>The covenant hosts the major ceremonies of the Order on a regular basis, such as Tribunals, ceremonies of welcome, and Hermetic fairs.</p>","source":"Cov","page":21,"indexKey":"ceremonies","review_status":"reviewed","reviewer":"lichen","type":"covenantExternalRelations","impact":{"value":"major"},"hidden":false,"tainted":false},"effects":[],"flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"12.343","systemId":"arm5e","systemVersion":"2.4.0.4","createdTime":1749287868926,"modifiedTime":1749370310659,"lastModifiedBy":"xMd6zrGNn4dbQYey"},"_id":"xMr5SrZotquCabDF","sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J":3}}
{"folder":"O5LhN2J2Ed3J2OWc","name":"Rebellious Covenfolk","type":"flaw","img":"systems/arm5e/assets/icons/base-magic.svg","system":{"description":"<p>Due to previous events in the covenant’s history, the Prevailing Loyalty of the covenant (see Chapter 3: Governance, Prevailing Loyalty) is shockingly low. Subtract sufficient loyalty points to obtain a loyalty point total of –75 (a Prevailing Loyalty of –5). Stories that involve the disloyalty of the covenfolk continue until morale is increased.</p>","source":"Cov","page":19,"indexKey":"rebellious-covenfolk","review_status":"reviewed","reviewer":"lichen","type":"covenantResidents","impact":{"value":"major"},"hidden":false,"tainted":false},"effects":[],"flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"12.343","systemId":"arm5e","systemVersion":"2.4.0.4","createdTime":1749287883937,"modifiedTime":1749370310664,"lastModifiedBy":"xMd6zrGNn4dbQYey"},"_id":"xXsSYQ4rgaMLE6du","sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J":3}}
{"folder":"FvLHeGVEQh6UL4Jd","name":"Urban","type":"flaw","img":"systems/arm5e/assets/icons/base-magic.svg","system":{"description":"<p>The covenant is in a city. The vast majority of the inhabitants are not part of the covenant, and the covenant does not rule the city.</p>","source":"Cov","page":10,"indexKey":"urban","review_status":"reviewed","reviewer":"lichen","type":"covenantSite","impact":{"value":"major"},"hidden":false,"tainted":false},"effects":[],"flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"12.343","systemId":"arm5e","systemVersion":"2.4.0.4","createdTime":1749287885314,"modifiedTime":1749370310672,"lastModifiedBy":"xMd6zrGNn4dbQYey"},"_id":"y2tFlJMwUserIG7l","sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J":3}}
{"folder":"r7IGd9SqC2sfaO6M","name":"Fallen Temple","type":"flaw","img":"systems/arm5e/assets/icons/base-magic.svg","system":{"description":"<p>There is an area near the covenant that was, for a lengthy period, a site of magical practice. The temple site has not been secured, so the covenant’s members cannot be sure what defenses or treasures wait there.</p>","source":"Cov","page":24,"indexKey":"fallen-temple","review_status":"reviewed","reviewer":"lichen","type":"covenantSurroundings","impact":{"value":"minor"},"hidden":false,"tainted":false},"effects":[],"flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"12.343","systemId":"arm5e","systemVersion":"2.4.0.4","createdTime":1749287886938,"modifiedTime":1749370310678,"lastModifiedBy":"xMd6zrGNn4dbQYey"},"_id":"yC5ppiJPborAGrBG","sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J":3}}
